title: mama's yeast and cinnamon rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast and sugar in water.
Then add flour, salt and shortening.
Let rise about 2 hours.
Use a little more flour to work the dough.
(You may use part of the dough for buns and part for cinnamon rolls.)
Roll out dough for rolls and spread with oleo. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up and cut in slices about 1-inch wide.
Put in a pan and let rise for about 1 hour, then bake.

title: angel hair basilicia
directions: Saute crushed garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, cut in large cubes.
Cook 15 minutes; keep tomatoes in chunks, don't mash. Salt to taste.
Add handful of basil; let simmer 2 to 3 minutes. Basil will turn black if you overcook.
Pour over cooked angel hair and top with grated cheese.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon fat in pan.
Stir in vinegar and sour cream. Mix in a bowl, the egg yolk, water and flour until smooth.
Stir into pan mixture and cook on low.
Stir constantly until dressing thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and salt.
Pour hot dressing over fresh lettuce and crumble bacon on top.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed chicken shells
directions: Mix chicken (diced), peas, mayonnaise and stuffing. Cook shells and fill with chicken mixture.
Place stuffed shells in an 11 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the soups and water with the reserved chicken broth.
Pour over the top of the shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 320° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well; make drop cookies (makes at least 6 dozen) by dropping by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: low calorie bleu cheese dressing
directions: Place ingredients in blender.
Blend at high speed until smooth.
Store, covered, in refrigerator for several hours before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Beat egg, milk and oil together.
Add cheese to flour, then add egg mixture and mix to a very soft consistency.
Put in patty tins and bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Heat milk to scalding hot. Melt butter in milk. Beat the whole eggs lightly. Beat in sugar, salt and nutmeg. Add egg mixture to scalded milk, stir until mixed. Pour into pastry shell and bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes, then at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients, except for bacon strips.
Pour bean mixture in 2-quart microwave dish.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir. Top with bacon strips and cook for 5 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter "girl scout" cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers.
Dip in melted chocolate and lay on waxed paper.
Can be frozen also.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a small bowl, combine all the ingredients.
Mix well. Place onto wax paper.
Shape into a rectangle 1/2-inch high. Chill at least 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: holiday date and nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients with buttermilk and vanilla.
Add chopped dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in
9 1/2 x 14 x 2-inch pan. Inserted knife should come out clean.

title: chicken dinner
directions: Place all ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake
at
375° for 45	to
50 minutes or until done.
(The
juice
from
the chicken should be clear when pierced deeply with a fork.)

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool. Peel and shred coarsely. Combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter, stirring occasionally until just melted. Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion and seasonings. Fold in potatoes and turn into a greased 2-quart casserole. Dot with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: chicken hannah
directions: Slice chicken
into chunks and layer in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Then pour soup mixed with milk over chicken. Place slices of Swiss cheese over chicken and soup.
Prepare stuffing as per package directions and place on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rice pilaf or over plain rice.

title: homestead vegetable soup
directions: Peel and dice all vegetables.
Melt butter in 4-quart pot. Saute all vegetables except potato (white).
Add rice, water and herbs.
Boil 1 1/2 hours.
Add white potato, boil for 15 minutes more.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
May add or change vegetables with what you have on hand.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add alternately with milk. Stir in flavorings.
Grease and flour tube pan well.
Cook for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: sausage soup
directions: Place potatoes and onions into 5-quart pot; add parsley.
Add enough water to cover.
Slice sausage into thin, about 1/8-inch ringlets and add to potato mixture.
Bring mixture to a boil; lower heat and cook until potatoes are soft.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove from stove, cover and let stand 30 minutes before serving.

title: chicken divan
directions: Line casserole dish with broccoli; add chicken.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: easy chocolate cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and eggs.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Once they are cool, ice them and enjoy!

title: stove top pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In nonstick frying pan, melt margarine or butter over low heat.
Arrange pineapple slices on bottom, using pecan or walnut halves to fill spaces.
Place one cherry in each pineapple hole. Scatter brown sugar over pineapple and nuts.
Add cake mix (prepared according to directions in cake mix box, substituting pineapple juice for some of the water required).
Cover and cook for 25 minutes or until cake tester or knife comes out clean when inserted.
Let cool.
Invert onto cake plate or server.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put hash browns in bottom of pan.
In a bowl, mix onions, salt, pepper, soup (no water), sour cream and cheese.
Spread on potatoes.
Melt margarine.
Crush Bran Flakes; mix with margarine.
Spread on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.
Enjoy!

title: three cheese and chicken bake
directions: Saute green peppers and onion in butter.
Stir in soup, milk and mushrooms.
Add pimento.
Place half of noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with half of each: mushroom sauce, cottage cheese, chicken and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Serve with refreshing tossed salad and chilled fruit.

title: always perfect roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line an oblong aluminum or glass pan with enough heavy-duty foil to be sealed in the middle of top. Spread half the can of soup over foil in bottom.
Cover with half the dry onion soup.
Place roast on top.
Spread remaining half can of soup onto the roast and cover with rest of onion soup. Seal tightly on top.
Place in oven for 2 to 3 hours, according to size of roast. Makes own gravy.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Beat until smooth.
Ice meat mixture.
Can decorate with chopped nuts, dried onions or anyway you desire.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1/2 of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with rest of cheese on top and broil until cheese melts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients over low heat.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool, then use.
Refrigerate extra.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening together thoroughly.
Put aside 1 1/2 cups.
Mix molasses, boiling water and soda.
Stir crumbs into liquid mixture until all are in but the 1 1/2 cups set aside. Pour into two unbaked pie shells and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes and then reduce heat to 325°.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Use either 2 deep dish pie shells or make up your own:
2 cups flour sifted with 1 teaspoon salt.
Cut in 3/4 cup shortening and work in 1/3 cup water.
Use 9-inch deep pie pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: conga bars
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chinese pork
directions: Mix soy sauce, honey, cinnamon, garlic, onions and ginger. Pour this marinade over pork. Marinate in refrigerator at least 6 hours or overnight. Place tenderloins in cooking bags with approximately 1/2 cup marinade. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pork is done.

title: cream cheese chewies
directions: Mix the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg to form dough.
Press into a greased 11 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the powdered sugar and cream cheese, then add the 2 eggs and vanilla.
Pour mixture over dough; sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool; cut into small squares.
They are better if they are cooled at room temperature, then placed in the refrigerator to keep.

title: turkey roll-ups
directions: Make stuffing according to directions on package.
Allow time to cool.
Put a large tablespoon of stuffing in the middle of the turkey.
Roll and place on a greased pan.
Cook at 325° for 15 minutes.
Serve with gravy.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and add egg last.
Pour mushroom soup over casserole.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef, onions and garlic until meat is browned and onions are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cut in squares.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli frittata
directions: Saute broccoli, onions, mushrooms, green pepper, salt and pepper in oil until broccoli is crisp-tender (5 to 10 minutes). Cool slightly.
Combine eggs, milk, cheese and basil; blend thoroughly.
Stir into mixture in skillet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted comes clean.
Makes 6.

title: chicken in paprika sauce
directions: Brown pieces of chicken in butter in a large skillet or Dutch oven.
Add peppers, onions, tomatoes and celery.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cornstarch and water, in a small saucepan.
Heat just to boiling point over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Pour sauce over chicken and vegetables.
Cover and continue cooking over low heat for about 1 hour, or until chicken is fork-tender.
If sauce is thin, thicken with cornstarch and water.
Good served with rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In blender, put milk, cheese and flour; cover and process at grind.
Add cooked broccoli and process again.
Add enough milk to fill the blender (1 cup).
Cook over low heat; stir until hot. Add 2 bouillon cubes, cream of celery and cream of mushroom soup. If soup is too thick, add more milk (slowly).
You can add more cheese if you want to.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Pare the rind and cut into 2-inch squares.
Soak in salt water overnight.
Drain then cook tender in boiling water, just enough to cover.
Put the vinegar and sugar in a kettle then add spices tied in a bag.
Boil mixture just 10 minutes then slowly cook about 1 hour or until syrup is thick.
Add the rind and simmer 1 hour; can.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump all ingredients into 9 x 13-inch ovenproof dish in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Yield: 15 servings.

title: macaroni & cheese
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2qt. baking dish.
Pour macaroni into melted butter - stir until coated.
Cut cheese into pieces.
Add salt, pepper, cheese & milk to macaroni.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hrs. uncovered.
Do not stir while baking!

title: jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks and jam.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 waxed paper-lined 9-inch layer cake pans.
Cool and frost with chocolate mocha or white icing..

title: italian vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown bacon pieces in large skillet; pour off all but 1 tablespoon bacon fat.
Stir in onion and garlic in fat until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Bring to boil, then simmer, uncovered, until zucchini is tender, about 20 minutes.
Pour soup into blender, 2 cups at a time.
Cover; blend on low speed until liquified, then blend on high until smooth. Serve hot with Parmesan cheese.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage (out of casing).
Add celery, cook 10 minutes. Add everything else, except mushrooms.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes. Add mushrooms; cook 10 to 15 more minutes.

title: autumn soup
directions: Cook meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook onion in meat until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except tomatoes. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes; stir and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: mushroom chicken breast
directions: Lightly flour chicken; season with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil; remove.
Add mushrooms and saute lightly.
Place rice in bottom of ovenproof baking dish.
Place mushrooms in 6 mounds evenly spaced in dish.
Place chicken on mounds.
Mix soups and wine.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove cover; sprinkle generously with cheese.
Return to oven for 5 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, sugar and salt. Work in shortening.
Add dissolved yeast to buttermilk, then add to dry ingredients.
Knead well and turn out onto floured board (adding additional flour if necessary to keep dough from sticking).
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick; cut to desired shape.
Dip in melted butter and fold to make pocketbook rolls.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
(Dough may be stored for a week in refrigerator covered before allowing to rise.)
For extra light biscuits, allow to rise 45 to 60 minutes before baking.

title: chinese nut balls(wedding cookies)
directions: Form in balls.
Cook at 275° for 30 minutes.
After cooling, roll twice in powdered sugar.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Combine drained pineapple with marshmallows.
Cover and set overnight.
Take pineapple juice, egg, vinegar, sugar and flour and heat until thick.
Cool overnight in fridge.
Next day, cut up apples and add marshmallow/pineapple mixture.
Add other mixture and mix together.
Add peanuts and Cool Whip.
Mix and serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice onions and fry in a little butter with the strips of meat which have been rolled in flour, salt and pepper.
Add bouillon and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Peel mushrooms and add 30 minutes before serving.
Stir in sour cream just before removing from the heat.
Serves 4.

title: simple corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Blend in flour and milk.
Add creamed corn, oleo, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in a dish.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing mix.
Spread dressing over salad, making sure the salad is completely covered.
Chill 24 hours.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray. In a large bowl, combine the pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, pumpkin pie spice and salt. Beat until mixed with a whisk. Pour into the pan. Sprinkle the top with the dry cake mix. Sprinkle with pecans. Pour margarine evenly over top and to the edges of the pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until the top is browned and the middle is set. Serve warm or cold. Top with Cool Whip when served.

title: wild violet jam
directions: *Be sure to use the common wild purple violet, not the American violet (often grown as a houseplant).

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone (cook with onion).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Put chicken back in mixture and soup.
Stir until it is blended well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake until hot or cheese is melted.

title: cornflake kisses(low carbs)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat egg white.
Gradually beat in sugar, then salt and vanilla.
Fold in cornflakes.
Take up heaping teaspoonfuls of mixture and push onto well-oiled baking sheet. Bake until surface is dry (about 20 min.).
Do not brown.
Remove from pan with side of spatula while kisses are still warm.
These freeze well.
Serves 18.
Serving size is 1 kiss at 18 calories each and the diet exchanges are free.

title: ora e. stewart's cherry slices
directions: Cream oleo and sugar, then add one egg at a time (beating as for pound cake), then rest of ingredients.
Spread 1/2 or little more of batter in oblong cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Spread on pie filling.
Put the rest of batter on top by spoonfuls, trying to cover the cherries.
Bake at 325° about one hour.
I put glaze of powdered sugar on top, when cooled.

title: trifle spectacular
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk; beat with mixer.
Mix together all the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; beat well with mixer.
Stir in diced zucchini.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick or cake tester comes out clean and dry. This really needs no frosting; it is moist and very tender.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, cocoa and eggs.
Add flour, nuts, Marshmallow Fluff and coconut.
Beat until mixed.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed dressing (tart)
directions: Puree or liquify
onion
in
small amount of vinegar in blender.
Mix sugar,
salt	and
dry
mustard together and mix well.
Add the rest
of the vinegar and lemon juice to blender and slowly blend in dry ingredients.
Add oil slowly and blend thoroughly.
Add poppy seed last.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella.
Combine corn flakes and butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Then add alternately dry ingredients, banana and milk.
Stir in nuts and pour into greased and floured large baking loaf pan or two smaller loaf pans.
Bake at 350° on 1 level below oven center for 1 hour.

title: prize karrot kake
directions: Mix carrots, sugar, flour, eggs, oil and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend bananas with all other ingredients. Put mixture in paper muffin cups in a muffin pan. Freeze.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almonds.
Mix well.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In bowl, mix soups (no water added), mixed vegetables and broth together.
Pour over chicken in 9x13-inch pyrex dish.
Mix oleo, buttermilk and flour.
Mix well.
Spoon over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes or until browned.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples; slice and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Arrange in 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Sift remaining sugar, flour and cinnamon; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then in moderate oven at 350°, for about 40 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: tuna skillet special
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet over medium flame; add onions, green peppers, red peppers (if used), pimientos and mushrooms.
Cook and stir until onions are transparent.
Mix tomato soup and cream together and stir into the onion mixture. Bring to a boil over medium flame and cook a few minutes.
Drain tuna; break into bite-size chunks and add to mixture in skillet. Stir in chutney.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir well to blend.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.
Good served over hot cooked rice or noodles.

title: jackie's waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour onto hot waffle griddle (approximately 1 cup batter for 4 waffles).
Cook approximately 4 minutes (or as your instructions direct).
Makes 24 waffles.
Can freeze and reheat in the toaster!

title: chicken potato salad
directions: Boil chicken until cooked.
Remove from pot and set aside to cool.
When chicken is cooled, dice and place in bowl.
Combine chicken, hard-boiled eggs, potatoes and chopped sweet pickle.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste, mayonnaise (to desired consistency) and olive oil.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: zucchini casserole for six
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in 4 tablespoons of the melted margarine until vegetables are barely tender.
Stir together the sour cream, soup and shredded carrot in a 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Toss remaining crumbs and butter together; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Put in Bundt pan.
Can be used in lamb cake pan for Easter.

title: fish-n-boats
directions: Combine tuna, mayonnaise, celery and pickle relish in mixing bowl.
Stir well with a fork; set aside.
Place French rolls on a cutting board.
Carefully cut a thin slice, lengthwise, off the top of each roll.
With your fingers, hollow out the rolls by removing some of the soft bread.
Leave about 1/2-inch
shell. Place the boats on a 10
x 15-inch baking sheet.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons shredded cheese into each boat.
Fill the boats with tuna mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining shredded cheese.
Place baking sheet in oven under hot broiler for 1 to 2 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Carefully remove from oven.
Cut slice of cheese diagonally.
Thread a wooden skewer through the cheese to make a sail.
Place a sail in each boat.
Top with sliced olives. Serves 4.

title: banana pudding
directions: Add milk to pudding mix.
Mix well until thickens.
In a serving bowl, put a layer of wafers, plenty of bananas and plenty of pudding.
Then repeat until the bowl is full.

title: georgia peach shortcake
directions: Arrange in an 8-inch greased pan.
Combine.
Let set to marinate.
Drop pieces of oleo over fruit.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: harvest popcorn
directions: Season popcorn with salt and butter in bowl.
Stir in peanuts. Sprinkle with mixture of remaining seasonings.
Spread in two 9 x 13-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Store in airtight containers.

title: carrot corn bread
directions: In medium bowl of electric mixer, combine carrots and corn meal; set aside.
In small saucepan, heat milk to boiling point. Add to corn meal mixture.
Stir thoroughly and bring to room temperature.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir to mix thoroughly.
Add eggs and vegetable oil to corn meal mixture and beat on medium speed until combined. Add flour mixture and beat thoroughly.
Pour into lightly greased, 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until bread tests done.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Drain some of juice from beans and mix with ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 30 minutes until warm.
Also excellent when heated in a crock-pot.
This is a Transportation Department favorite.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Add flour, salt, milk and vanilla, gradually.
Mix well.
Mix vinegar and soda in a small bowl.
Add to other ingredients by hand.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and put into a hollowed out loaf of bread.
Put pieces of bread that were removed around the loaf and cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Cream together the 1 1/4 cups brown sugar, oil, vanilla, egg and buttermilk.
Add the flour, rhubarb, salt, soda and baking powder.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Put in shallow baking dish, sprinkle with grated cheese and crushed chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: cheese french fries
directions: Scrape out center of orange, grapefruit or onion and eat. Place egg in center and wrap in foil. Leave space for air in package.
Cook on coals for 5 or 10 minutes.

title: grandma ever's refrigerator stew
directions: Put all together in electric skillet or Dutch oven.
Simmer down at least 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit slushies
directions: Combine fruit, pop and ice cubes in blender.
Taste.
If sour, add sugar to taste.

title: old fashioned cole slaw
directions: Combine vegetables and cover with salt.
Pack in earthen or stone jar and weight.
Let stand at least 2 hours (or longer, may stand overnight.)
Drain thoroughly.

title: crabmeat supper pie
directions: Sprinkle cheese evenly over bottom of pastry shell.
Top with crabmeat and sprinkle green onions.
Combine eggs, cream, salt, lemon peel and dry mustard.
Pour over crabmeat.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: swedish cabbage casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown the ground beef and onions; drain excess fat.
Add stewed tomatoes and rice, stirring to break up tomatoes and blend ingredients.
Bring to boil, cover and turn off heat and let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in next 5 ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.
Arrange cabbage in bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan.
Spread hamburger mixture over cabbage, cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in greased 8 x 14-inch pan.
Cool.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dice 1 to 3 cucumbers in thin slices.
Mix with 1 tablespoon salad dressing.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: angel food jello cake
directions: Make Jell-O with 3 1/2 cups of water.
Add frozen berries and stir.
Gel until consistency of egg whites.
Add 10 ounces of Cool Whip.
Fold in torn-up cake.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Fold in soft ice cream.
Add strawberries.
Put in graham cracker crust. Keep refrigerated. Very good.

title: apple yum yum cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Make a hole or well in center of dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix together in "well".
Now, mix all together just until all is moist.
Mix in apples and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan (angel food cake pan) at 350° for 75 minutes or until done (mixture will be "globby" and blend with a fork).
You can put a sugar glaze on it if you like.
It's good warm and spread butter on it, or cold.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender, adding ice cubes a few at a time.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Mix oleo and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Add layer of chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over top evenly. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: lemon yum yum
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch oblong Pyrex dish.

title: cheese-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
Drain and place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine eggs, milk, soup, mayonnaise and cheese. Stir together well.
Pour mixture over broccoli and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meal in a bag
directions: You will need 4 sheets tinfoil.

title: baked asparagus dip
directions: Blend asparagus, cheese and mayonnaise.
Place in a 2-cup ovenproof bowl.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve with snack rye breads.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cool.
Prepare crust as directed on package.
Spoon cooled sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together. Pour over potatoes and cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Slice and serve.

title: holiday wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes. Strain and discard spices. Serve hot. Yield: about 3 quarts.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put 2 sticks of margarine in 9x13 inch pan and melt in oven.
Mix milk, 1 c. sugar, salt, flour, and baking powder together.
Pour over melted margarine.
Put 2-4 cups of fruit on top of batter.
Sprinkle with 1 c. sugar.
Add 1 c. water.
Bake until dough rises to top and browns, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: romaine salad
directions: Clean romaine and cut into bite-size.
Drain and place in refrigerator until crisp.
When ready to serve, place in bowl. Mix all ingredients.
Toss and serve.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Pour fruit juices and water into a 10-cup percolator.
Place sugar, cloves, 1/2 stick cinnamon and salt in percolator basket. Perk through complete cycle.
Serve hot with cinnamon stick stirrers.
Yield:
8 cups.

title: eloise salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Mix with dry Jell-0O.
Mix all together and chill.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter in casserole dish and put in oven to melt.
Sift flour and mix with sugar.
Stir in milk slowly and thoroughly.
After butter is melted, remove from oven and pour flour mixture over butter, then pour peaches (juice also) over flour mixture and return to oven.
Bake for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken.
Simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: grandma's potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in water. Cut and cube.
When tender, add remaining ingredients.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook until very thick.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add drained corn and cheese.
Stir in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: german chocolate cheese cake
directions: First Layer:
Spread coconut and pecans in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken with mushroom-dijon sauce
directions: Combine
water,
wine,	onion,	lemon
juice,
bouillon granules, thyme and
peppercorns
in
skillet.
Bring to boil. Cover; reduce heat and
simmer
5 minutes.	Add chicken; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until done.
Remove chicken;
reserve liquid. Strain liquid.
Discard onion, peppercorns and thyme. Add honey, mustard and
mushrooms to cooking liquid.
Bring to boil; cook 10 minutes.

title: quick and easy cheese cake
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.
Pour in graham cracker pie crust.
Chill 20 minutes.

title: chili with meat(chili con carne)
directions: Melt the butter or margarine in the bottom of a large saucepan. Add the onions and cook until they are tender and transparent.
Add the meat and continue to cook until the meat loses its redness. Add the salt and chili powder.
Continue to cook for a few seconds longer.
Add the potatoes, green pepper, celery, tomatoes and the tomato soup.
Simmer for 15 minutes longer, or until the edges of the potato cubes become transparent.
Add the beans and simmer for 15 minutes more.

title: kim's delight
directions: Mix the sugar and cream cheese fully. Combine pecans, Cool Whip and pineapple to mixture. Fill the pie crust with the filling. Put in the refrigerator about 30 minutes. Serve and enjoy.

title: chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Mix vanilla and sour cream.
Add sour cream and dry ingredients.
Dust chocolate chips with 1 teaspoon flour, fold in.
Bake in greased cupcake pan for 23 to 25 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix lightly, but well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, baking powder and nuts.
Mix together.
Divide batter in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients till creamy.
Measure out flour and add the rest of the dry ingredients.
Measure out 1 c. sour milk. If not available, add 2 Tbsp. vinegar to 1 c. milk and add 1 tsp. soda to milk.
Now add flour mixture and milk to the batter until mixed.
Set overnight in the refrigerator.	You can roll these out and cut them out.
I use large scoop and drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 8-10 minutes.
Put grease or shortening on bottom of glass, dip in sugar and pat down.
Makes about 5-7
large cookies.

title: russian fudge
directions: Mix condensed milk and sugar in heavy skillet.
Allow to melt over medium heat, then turn heat higher so that a brown crust will form on bottom of pot.
Scrape (do not stir) constantly.
After cooking approximately 10 minutes, when mixture will become light caramel color and forms a soft ball in a cup of cold water. Remove from fire and mash all brown lumps with back of spoon.
Add salt, butter and pecans, stirring 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into buttered platter and cool.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk in a large bowl until pudding is mixed well.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip and blend well.
Layer cookies, pudding and bananas in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with wafers.

title: baked salmon loaf(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix salmon with cracker crumbs, milk and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into loaf.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat.
Blend in melted chocolate.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut.

title: cherry pizza cake
directions: Place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan in order given. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until brown and crunchy.

title: basic sourdough starter
directions: Leave out of refrigerator for 24 hours.
Makes 3 to 4 cups.

title: the bible cake
directions: Cream A and B.
Beat C and D until frothy.
Add E, mixing well.
Add to creamed mixture; beat well.
Sift F with G and add to first mixture.
Chop I.
Sprinkle with a little F and add to H along with J, 1 teaspoon each.
Beat 5 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Cut in first three ingredients.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip with electric beater.
Spread carefully onto the cooled crust.
Mix and let set 3 small size lemon instant pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk per package.
Pour over cream mixture and then spread the rest of the Cool Whip over the pudding and use 1/4 cup nuts for decoration.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix cottage cheese with dry jello.
Add pineapple and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in dish and refrigerate.

title: end of the garden relish
directions: Soak cucumber, pepper, onion and cabbage in salt water (1/2 cup salt to 2 quarts water) for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Turn heat on low and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add raw, soaked vegetables.
Boil again for 15 minutes.
Put in hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: fluffy egg whites
directions: Cook cornstarch and sugar until clear.
Let cool.
Beat 3 egg whites until stiff peaks form, then add sugar mixture.
Beat until stiff.

title: purple cow shakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high speed for 30 seconds.
Serve in cold glasses with straws.
Enjoy! Refreshing drink on a hot summer day!

title: missy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cream nut rolls
directions: Scald cream. Cool to lukewarm. Crumble yeast into cooled cream. Cream butter thoroughly. Add yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour alternately with yeast mixture to creamed butter mixture. Beat thoroughly. Chill dough overnight in refrigerator.
Mix sugar and nutmeats. Sprinkle half on breadboard.
Divide chilled dough in half. Roll out each portion on the sugar and nutmeat mixture to about 1/8-inch thick. Roll as for jelly roll. Cut 1/2-inch slices.
Place on baking sheet 1 1/2-inches apart.
Let rise until light, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until browned.

title: hawaiian party salad
directions: Combine rice, chicken, grapes, celery and pecans.
Blend together mayonnaise, lemon juice and seasonings.
Pour over rice mixture; toss lightly.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce cups.
Garnish with clusters of grapes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter or margarine with the brown sugar. Mix in the pretzels and pat mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Set aside to cool.

title: easy chicken and vegetables
directions: Put chicken breasts in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add vegetables, all sliced.
Vegetable types and amounts can vary according to your taste.
Douse with soy sauce.
Add several pats of margarine. Seal pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grilled marinated steak
directions: Rub steaks with garlic salt and meat tenderizer.
Pierce with fork; let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Combine soy sauce, 1/2 cup water, vinegar and sugar; pour over steak.
Let marinate for 30 minutes.
Grill on each side.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain liquid from beets into sauce pan.
Season liquid with the remaining ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil, then thicken with:
2 Tbsp. Argo Starch that you have mixed with a little water.
Stir into hot liquid and cook until thickened the way you want it.
Pour beets into hot liquid and cook.
Stir until thickened.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove from bone.
Place in bottom of large casserole dish; season with salt and pepper.
Cover with 1/2 stick margarine, chicken broth and cream of chicken soup. Stir flour and milk together; pour over chicken and soup mixture. Cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 8 to 10 generous servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer in order.
Place in refrigerator, covered, for 24 hours, then toss.

title: sour cream cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add lemon juice and cranberry sauce.
Mix well.
Chill until thick.
Fold in sour cream.
Add nuts and stir.
Pour into oiled 1/2-quart mold.
Serves 12.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix sugar, baking powder and flour.
Add eggs and beat well, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour in pastry shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
These pies freeze well.

title: dilly beans
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in each pint.
Snip ends of beans. Place in cold water and bring to boil.
Boil for 15 minutes. Drain.
Pack lengthwise into sterilized pint jars.
Then bring 3 cups water, vinegar and salt to a boil and boil for 5 minutes. Pour over beans and seal tightly.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and add enough chicken broth to soften to desired consistency.
Put in baking pan and cook at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix flour & sugar.
Add potatoes, eggs, corn syrup, nutmeg, salt, butter and milk.
Beat well.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350 degrees for 50-60 minutes or until set.

title: oriental cole slaw
directions: Mix together.
Crush the Ramen noodles and add to mixture; let stand 1 hour (or longer).
Add:

title: fran's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the softened butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla extract, mixing well.
Add the flour, baking soda and salt, mixing until well blended.
Add chocolate chips and chopped nuts (if desired).
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: padang beef
directions: Saute in oil the garlic, turmeric, ginger and lemon grass. Add meat, chilies and salt. Saute 3 minutes. Add coconut milk and bay leaf. Cover and simmer until sauce is thick. May be served hot or cold. Serves 4 to 6.

title: best ever apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil together.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a greased pan.

title: church windows
directions: Melt butter in top of a double boiler over hot water.
Add chocolate morsels; stir until melted, then remove from heat.
Let cool.
Add marshmallows; stir lightly.

title: york hermits cookies
directions: Work butter into flour, soda and salt.
Add sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: jalapeno squares
directions: Use a good honey cured ham and bake according to directions. Smoked Turkey:
See recipe.
Set out assorted mustards, mayonnaise and small rolls.

title: savory lima beans
directions: Melt butter in a 3-cup saucepan with cover.
Add onion and green pepper; cover and cook a few minutes.
Add tomatoes, dill weed, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add lima beans.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Put all ingredients, except ice, into blender container. Cover and process at liquefy until all ingredients are liquefied. Remove lid and add ice.
Continue to process until ice is liquefied.

title: holiday wreaths
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows; remove from heat.
Add enough food coloring to turn green.
Add corn flakes and mix well.
Shape mixture into small wreaths.
Put 3 of miniature cinnamon pieces on top.
Let cool on wax paper.

title: dump it cake
directions: Spread pineapple on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pie filling on top of pineapple layer.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of fruit.
Sprinkle nuts on top of cake mix.
Cut butter into 6 slices lengthwise.
Place the 12 slices of butter on top of the nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 8 x 13-inch pan with oil and flour.
Pour pineapple chunks and juice in pan.
Sprinkle nuts over pineapple.
Pour in dry cake mix.
Smooth surfaces but don't mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pepperidge farm dressing
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Mix soup with broth.
Layer dressing, chicken and mushroom soup.
Repeat layers with dressing layer on top.
Cook in oven at 350° to 400° until hot.
If too dry, pour broth over top or melted chicken bouillon cube.

title: steak or what?
directions: Pat the ground beef evenly into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread potatoes, onion, peas and mushrooms evenly over beef.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix the soups together; spread evenly over the top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apricot cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add softened Knox gelatine.
Add marshmallows; beat while still hot.
Cool; add fruits.
Chill until firm in refrigerator.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Combine fruit.	Cut
nuts.
Sift
salt, flour, soda and cinnamon together.	Cream
butter.	Add sugar until mixture is smooth.
Beat in
eggs
one at a time.
Stir in flour mixture. Mix in fruit
and
nuts thoroughly.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.)

title: cajun bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans for several hours.
Drain and place in 3-quart pot.
Cover with 2-quarts of water.
Add ham bone, 1/2 of the onions, celery and bell pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until soft.
Freezes well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease	and
flour
a 10-inch tube pan.
Whisk together corn oil
and
sugar.
Stir
together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking
soda
and salt.
Stir 1/2 the dry ingredients into	the sugar-oil
mixture	and blend.
Alternately stir in rest of
dry ingredients
while adding eggs, one by one.
Mix well.
Add carrots, raisins and nuts.	Pour into prepared pan and bake at 360° for 70 minutes.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream cheese and sugar together.
Fold in cool whip.
Keep this in the refrigerator while draining canned
fruit in colander. (save the fruit juice for the kids)

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Mix crumbs and sugar and add melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Put 2 1/2 cups of chocolate pudding on crumbs and spread evenly.
Mix 1 1/2 cups of chocolate pudding with 2 cups of Dream Whip.
Spread evenly on top of pudding.
Then spread the rest evenly with remainder of Dream Whip.
Put a drop of syrup on and run a toothpick and make cobwebs on top with chocolate chips and nuts.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix butter and sugar. Add in flour. Put in 9-inch cake pan. Prick with fork all over. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat strawberries with an electric mixer until berries are in small pieces.
Mix with eggs and oil; add to dry mixture, stirring carefully to mix.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Loaves can be frozen.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine the peanut butter, dry milk and the honey in a medium bowl.
Knead the mixture by hand.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Roll the balls in powdered sugar.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: fudge pie
directions: Grease 8-inch cake pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Toast walnuts in oven for 10 minutes; cool.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt. Beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Stir in toasted walnuts. Turn into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool on wire rack.
Remove from pan.
Spoon ice cream onto center of pie; cut into pie-shaped wedges.

title: custard filled cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, sift together cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and pour in buttermilk and eggs.
Stir until almost blended.
Stir in 1 cup milk and kernels until just combined.
Do not overmix.
Pour butter into a 10-inch cast-iron skillet and melt in oven.
Swirl to coat bottom and sides.
Scrape batter into skillet and sprinkle with remaining milk.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot with sweet butter.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: brandied fruit
directions: Drain juice from all of the fruit. Put fruit in a large jar or container that seals well. Add 1 cup sugar of each cup of fruit. Let stand. DO NOT REFRIGERATE. This is so good served on pound cake.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together the lemon juice and mayonnaise until well combined. Add the remaining ingredients, except the walnuts and toss to coat. Cover and chill for at least 1 hour before serving. Just before serving, sprinkle chopped walnuts over the top.

title: irish potato pancakes
directions: Pare and grate potatoes.
Mix in flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Heat griddle or heavy skillet. Add 2 tablespoons oil. When oil bubbles, drop potato mixture into it by the tablespoon. Don't crowd.
Let cook over low heat until browned on both sides, turning only once. Spread with butter immediately and keep hot. Continue making pancakes, adding oil as needed.

title: green rice(not president bush's dish)
directions: Saute onion and celery in small amount of low-fat cooking oil. Mix Cheez Whiz in rice while still hot; stir in cooked broccoli. Add onion and celery; fold in mushroom soup.
Add a very small amount of water (like rinsing out soup can, approximately 2 to 3 tablespoons).
Stir all together and pour into greased casserole dish (2 or 3-quart size).
Bake in 350°
oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with grated cheese or bread crumbs, or both.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grind bologna, cheese and cream cheese together.
Add pizza sauce to mixture until moistened.
Spread on open sandwich buns. Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil in large skillet until well browned.
Put carrots and onions in bowl with small amount of water; microwave 3 minutes.
Add peppers and microwave 1 minute. Drain pineapple juice into bowl.
Add vinegar, sugar, ginger, soy sauce, garlic powder and cornstarch; stir well.
Pour into chicken and bring to a full boil while stirring.
Add vegetables and pineapple.
Stir well.
Serve chicken over rice.
Serves 4.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients and put peaches in last.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn salad
directions: Cook corn and cut off the cob or may use frozen or canned; fresh is better.
Do not peel cucumber.
Cut in half and slice. Add chopped red pepper and toss.
When ready to serve, add dressing.
May use store bought if preferred.
Very colorful and tasty.

title: air freshener - tree decoration
directions: Mix well. Roll out thin like cookie dough. Cut with cookie cutter.
Put hole in top to run ribbon through. Allow to air dry. May be painted for tree decoration or air freshener.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Crush Ritz crackers on top.
Melt oleo and drizzle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ice cream cake
directions: 1st Step:
Stir until well mixed the whipping cream, cocoa and sugar.
Refrigerate for 2 hours, then whip for icing.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch . Add milk, egg yolks, salt, vanilla and butter.
Cook until it thickens and comes to a boiling point. Pour into pie shell.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients and cut in Crisco.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Stir with wooden spoon until all flour is dampened.
Knead on floured board for a minute or two.
Roll out to desired thickness and cut out.
Bake in a lightly greased pan at 400° about 15 minutes.
The dough may be put in refrigerator immediately after mixing and used as needed. Keeps at least one week.

Dough can be cut into biscuits and put on wax paper or baking sheet to freeze about 2 hours, then put into airtight container to keep in freezer until ready to use. Let biscuits set out on lightly greased pan for a few minutes to thaw before baking.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown. Yield: about 24 biscuits.

title: barbecued sauerkraut
directions: Brown together the meat and onion.
Drain sauerkraut and mix with remaining ingredients.
Mix everything together and bake in casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Heat coffee and molasses to a boil.
Remove from heat; add dates and let cool.
Mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; then dry ingredients.
Add dates and nuts last.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Cut into squares when cool and roll in 10x sugar.

title: simmering potpourri bricks
directions: You will also need a mixing bowl, wooden spoon and cookie sheet.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit well.
Save only the pineapple juice.
Combine juice with vanilla pudding mix.
Beat 2 minutes until smooth.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in fruit.
Decorate top with cherries.
Delicious with Lemon Lightning Cake.

title: stew
directions: This may be baked at 250° for 5 hours or at 300° for 3 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes last (bake for the last 45 minutes to an hour).

title: imitation crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Spread thinly on two cookie pans (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1-inch).
Broil in oven until cheese is melted and top is nicely browned (about 5 minutes).
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: barbecued mushrooms
directions: Clean the mushrooms and cut in slices. Microwave on high for 4 minutes in a covered dish. Stir halfway through, drain liquid. Saut garlic in oil. Add mushrooms, salt, pepper, and onion powder. Mix and add catsup. Continue saut until catsup is absorbed and sticks to bottom of pan. (More catsup can be added if necessary.)

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Top each browned pork chop with 1 slice onion, 1 slice lemon, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup.
Add water. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: Brown beef.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 2 hours. Serves 10.
Tastes even better when reheated.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots, then drain.
Cook onion in 1 tablespoon margarine, then add soup, pepper and cheese.
Add carrots; put in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine and coat stuffing.
Cover casserole with stuffing and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in bottom of buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients and egg together until crumbly.
Pour over apples. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Heat 7-Up and pour over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.

title: cheese and ham party log
directions: Grate Spam and combine all ingredients except pecans.
Mix well and roll into a log shape or ball.
Then roll in chopped pecans.
Serve on platter with your choice of greenery, such as lettuce, endive, parsley, etc. as garnish.

title: olive cheese nuggets
directions: Blend butter and cheese.
Add flour, salt and paprika.
Blend and mix well to form dough.
Using about 1 teaspoon of dough, flatten dough out in the palm of your hand and wrap it around each olive.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
May be served hot or cold. May be made ahead and frozen, baked or unbaked.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large Dutch oven or saucepan.
Add soups, chicken broth, chicken (coarsely chopped) and Ro-Tel.
Heat until bubbly.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread. Spread tops of bread slices with margarine and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well. Spoon over bread slices. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Combine eggs, half and half and salt.
Mix well.
Pour over cheese. Cover casserole tightly and chill overnight.

title: snickers dessert (or salad)
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: stabilized whipped cream
directions: Sprinkle gelatine on cold water.
Let sit until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add the hot water; mix well, heat if needed, until all granules are dissolved.
Beat the whipping cream until nearly finished.
Slowly add the gelatine mixture, then add sugar to taste.
Beat until cream is of desired consistency.
Refrigerate.

title: cornmeal griddle cakes
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Beat egg.
Add milk and pour all at once into dry ingredients.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth. Stir in melted shortening.
Bake on a very lightly greased, moderately hot griddle (300° to 325°).
Bake until golden brown on under side and dry looking on top.
Then turn and bake until other side is brown.
Serve immediately with hot syrup.
Makes 24 (4-inch) cakes.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix ham, softened butter (not melted), mustard, onion, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce together in a bowl.
Split the whole package of rolls (treat as a single sheet).
Spread mixture on both sides.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese on one half.
Put bread top on.
Cut in squares.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Can freeze but thaw before baking.
Heat (in foil) for 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 60 small rolls for hors d'oeuvres.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Remove chicken breast bone and place small piece of cheese inside breast.
Roll breast and wrap with 1 slice of bacon. Place slices of dried beef in casserole dish.
Place rolled breasts on top of beef.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream; pour over rolled breasts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine butter, confectioners sugar and flour.
Put dough into pizza pan.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Let cool.

title: lollipops
directions: You will need 18 lollipop sticks.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Combine pie mix, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in medium saucepan.
Stir in egg yolks.
Add 2 cups water.
Cook on medium heat until it comes to full boil; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites with mixer until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Slowly fold into hot pudding mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate about 3 hours or until set.

title: chicken livers in wine
directions: Wash chicken livers thoroughly; cut in pieces.
Heat oil and oleo in skillet; add livers.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Cook over high heat until almost done and add wine; reduce heat to medium-high until liquid has reduced and livers are starting to brown.
Remove from heat.
Cooking time is approximately 10 minutes.

title: pizza casserole(by jo stephens, talmo, ga)
directions: Brown ground beef.
Spoon beef into 8-inch dish.
Top with cheese and pizza sauce.
Combine biscuit mix, milk and eggs; beat until smooth.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. Quick and easy to make.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Combine rice and onion in ground beef with salt and pepper seasoning.

After soaking green peppers in salted water at least 1/2 hour, stuff with meat mixture and put in tomatoes or tomato juice to cook slowly for 2 or more hours, either on top of the stove or in the oven.

title: skillet corn and tomatoes
directions: Fry corn in an iron skillet until tender.
Add remaining items.
Cook until desired thickness.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large glass bowl.
Mix or toss well.
Remove from freezer about 1 hour before serving.
Refreeze after serving.

title: baby corn delight
directions: In a heavy skillet, stir-fry the baby corn with oil and butter. Add onion, green pepper and garlic, then add tomato and stir-fry for 10 seconds.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Put milk and cornstarch in a bowl and mix until smooth.
Add to baby corn mixture and return to heat, stirring constantly.
Add envelope of Sazon and chicken flavoring.
Add sour cream and mix well, then the Feta cheese continuing to stir, mixing well.
When it begins to boil, turn stove off and continue stirring for one minute.
Let cool a few minutes and serve as a side dish or as desired. Delicious.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix and toss.
Keep mixing every 1/2 hour until the oil is absorbed.

title: old english caramel apples
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients (the sugars and cornstarch) in a medium saucepan.
Gradually stir in half and half and butter.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Core and cube apples.
Place in individual serving dishes.
Pour 1/4 cup sauce mixture over each apple serving.

title: cheese and ortega casserole
directions: Place in layers:
cheese and peppers.
Mix together Bisquick, eggs, salt and milk. Pour over the layered cheese and Ortegas. Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: root beer float
directions: In a tall soda glass, stir together the chocolate syrup with 1 scoop of the ice cream until smooth. Gradually pour in about 1/2 of the root beer until the glass is half full. Add the remaining soup of the ice cream and fill to the top with root beer. SUMMER BREEZE

title: crispettes
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugars and remaining ingredients. Beat well and drop by tablespoon on buttered pan 2-inches apart. Bake in moderate oven.

title: sunday brunch souffle
directions: Line greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan with bread.
Cover with cheeses and the options of your choice.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 12.
Salsa makes a tasty garnish.

title: disappearing brownies
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butterscotch chips and 1/4 cup oleo.
Cool.
Add 3/4 cup flour, 1/3 cup brown sugar, 1 egg, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix, then add 1 cup of miniature marshmallows, 1 cup chocolate chips and 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Double recipe and bake in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan for 25 minutes for more people.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mix over graham crackers.
Add another layer of whole graham crackers.
Add the rest of the pudding mix.
Top with whole graham crackers. Spread icing (see below) on top of crackers and chill.

title: turtle cake
directions: In a saucepan, mix together caramels and 1/4 cup evaporated milk (remainder to be used later).
Heat until caramels are melted; then set aside.

title: tater tot hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix milk with soup. Add all ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 2-quart casserole.

title: chocolate rum torte
directions: Tear cake into small pieces and toss with rum.
Melt chocolate over low heat or in double boiler.
Turn chocolate into bowl and add eggs one at a time, using medium speed on mixer.
Beat in vanilla.
In separate bowl, beat 1 pint heavy cream until frothy. Add sugar and beat to soft peaks.
Fold chocolate mixture into cream.
Layer chocolate mixture and cake into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Turn out onto serving platter and frost with remaining cream which has been whipped. Garnish with the almonds.
Freeze at least 30 minutes (longer, if desired) covered with plastic wrap.

title: all american raisin pie
directions: In a large saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. Blend in cranberry apple juice.
Add raisins and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Add almond extract. Cool slightly.
Pour mixture into pastry lined pie pan and cover with top crust.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake 20 minutes longer or until pastry is golden brown.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brown hamburger and onion together with salt and pepper. Drain grease. Mix all remaining ingredients. Put in a greased 2-quart casserole dish and bake.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 2-quart casserole dish and put in 325° oven (glass dish in 300° oven).
Bake for 3 hours.
Stir approximately every 20 minutes during first 2 hours.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine light brown sugar, egg, milk, vanilla and butter flavor Crisco in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine oatmeal, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough on a baking sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook 3 to 4 hours on high (or bring to a boil on top of stove, then transfer to crock-pot and cook on low 6 to 8 hours).
Taste for seasoning; adjust before serving.
Serve over cooked rice with shredded cheese and minced green onion.

title: orange julius
directions: Fill blender with ingredients and add ice to 5 cup line. Frapper to an icy texture.

title: red neck caviar
directions: Mix together and pour 8 oz Italian dressing over.
Chill overnight and serve.

title: 20 minute chocolate cake
directions: Melt oleo, cocoa, water and sugar in saucepan (large enough to hold all ingredients).
Add dry ingredients (flour and soda sifted together), then buttermilk. Next add eggs and vanilla.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Don't wash saucepan.
Make icing up in it.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chicken breasts in skillet.
Layer spinach in bottom of casserole which has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Mix cornstarch and a little milk.
Pour rest of milk into a sauce pan and begin to heat.
Add cornstarch mixture to milk which is heating, stirring constantly.
Add bouillon, caraway seed and cheese.
Heat, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted and sauce is smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Heat in preheated oven for about 20 minutes, just to warm.
You may adjust amount of sauce to taste.

title: oven beef stew
directions: You don't even brown the meat.
Just put all the ingredients in a large Dutch oven with a cover or a casserole.
Cook in the oven for 2 1/2 hours at 375°, stirring occasionally.

title: buffalo-style chicken wings
directions: Split wings at joint and discard tips. Arrange on a rack in a roasting pan. Cover wing pieces with sauce on both sides. Bake at 425° for 1 hour, turning halfway through cooking time. Wings can be deep-fried at 400° for about 12 minutes and then dipped into the hot sauce until coated completely. Serve with celery and Blue cheese dip.

title: corn fritters
directions: Cut corn from cob; drain.
Add egg yolk.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in egg white.
Drop from tablespoon into fat heated to 370°.
Cook until delicately brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: cocoa brownies(healthier recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil bottom only of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add oil and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Bake for 22 to 26 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel, broth and onion. In a casserole dish, put layers of soft taco shells, soup mixture and chicken.
Top with cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and keep out 1/4 cup for topping.
Mix the rest with 1/3 stick of melted butter.
Press into bottom of cake pan for bottom layer.
Slice the vanilla ice cream and press on top of cookies.
Streusel the caramel topping over the ice cream until covered.
Spread Cool Whip; then sprinkle Oreos on top.

title: ribbon meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together the bread and milk.
Mix in remaining ingredients (except Filling).
Pat 1/2 of meat mixture in greased loaf pan.
Cover with Cheese Filling.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, onions, salt, oregano, pepper and 1/3 cup tomato sauce.
Place mixture on wax paper and flatten into a rectangle.
Add cheese and roll like a jelly roll. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Pour off grease.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over meat loaf.
Return to oven.
Bake another 10 minutes.
It helps if you pinch the ends together so that the cheese does not come out.

title: spicy cheese, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Saute onion in margarine. Blend in the Cheez Whip, soup, water and seasoning until smooth. Gently fold in the broccoli and rice. Bake for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: betty's pecan goldies
directions: Let butter and cream cheese soften.
Mix together with flour and mold into small muffin pans or cupcake pans.

title: cereal
directions: Pour cereal into bowl and then pour milk over it and eat it up!
It's yummy!

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple tidbits and fruit cocktail well and mix together.
Peel pears, apples and bananas and cut in small cubes; slice strawberries.
Peel and slice kiwi.
Add all fresh fruit except kiwi to fruit cocktail and pineapple; mix.
Add Cool Whip; stir well and cover top with sliced kiwi.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Cook for 3 1/2 hours.

title: low-fat zucchini muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, combine beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and balance of ingredients (vegetables and fruits).
Spray (12-count) muffin pan with Pam. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need flower pot/sand bucket, artificial flowers, toy shovel and gummy worm.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Mix well and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish in oven at 350°.
Pour butter into bowl.
In another bowl, beat eggs; add sugar, flour and evaporated milk and mix well.
Add 2 cans of creamed corn and pour into casserole dish and pour remaining butter on top.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Gently pull off eight large cabbage leaves.
Simmer in 1 inch of boiling water, covered, for 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: extra-rich chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add milk, egg yolks, vanilla and margarine.
Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and bake for 15 minutes at 250°.

title: borsch(ukrainian)
directions: Brown beef bones.
Add 3 cups water and simmer at least 1 hour.
Remove bones. Cool broth and skim off all fat.
Cut off meat from bones and cut into small pieces. Add to cooled broth. Saute chopped onion in oil until golden.
Add beets, carrot and celery.
Cook 5 minutes.

Add 6 cups boiling water, 1 whole onion, 1 bay leaf, dill, lemon juice and tomatoes. Simmer 15 minutes. Add cabbage and simmer another 20 minutes. Remove the bay leaf, whole onion and dill stalk. Add remaining mixture to the beef broth. Add potatoes and, if desired, a can of mixed vegetables. Heat.
Serve with a dollop of sour cream.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Beat 2 minutes.
Drain 1 can peaches and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into a baked pie shell and refrigerate for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Save a few peaches to garnish on top.

title: candied pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Stir in pecans, coating well.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon and stir in pecans, coating evenly.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk, dates and butter to a soft ball stage; add pecans, salt and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Pour on a clean tea towel and roll up.
Chill in the refrigerator.
Best to leave overnight.
When ready to eat just slice off a slice about 1/3 to 1/2 inch thick.

title: baked swiss steak
directions: Roll steak in flour.
Brown in skillet in small amount of fat. Put in baking dish, greased a little.
Add chopped onion (cut in medium size pieces), celery and carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to steak.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except for 1 c. pecans and mix well. Refrigerate until firm. Shape into a ball and roll in remaining pecans.

title: overseas fudge
directions: Place margarine, sugar and condensed milk in large pan.
Cook slowly.
Stir constantly (must) until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water (approximately 20 minutes).
Mix in bowl just lightly after it forms a soft ball.
Pour over Marshmallow Creme, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Beat as you add nuts.
When it starts to thicken, pour into buttered dish.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed of electric mixer for 5 minutes. Turn on low speed and gradually beat in sugar. Add pumpkin, lemon juice, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Beat on high speed until well blended. Grease and flour 9x12 inch pan. Sides of pan must measure 1/2 to 1 inch high. Pour mixture into pan and sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 375° about 15 minutes. Dump hot cake onto paper towels sprinkled with powdered sugar. Roll up and let cool completely. Mix together the cream cheese, powdered sugar, butter and vanilla. Unroll cake and discard paper towels. Spread mixture over cake and roll again.

title: baked barbecue beans
directions: Fry bacon and onion together.
Boil ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar together for a few minutes.
Mix that with the beans and add the browned hamburger.
Mix everything together and bake in a casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: scrambled egg muffins
directions: In a skillet, brown the sausage; drain. In a bowl, beat the eggs. Add onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Stir in sausage and cheese. Spoon by 1/3 cupfuls into greased muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. YIELD: 1 dozen.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Italian dressing for 1 to 2 hours, turning frequently.
Combine equal amounts of wheat germ and corn flakes in a plastic bag.
Shake pieces of chicken in mixture, coating evenly.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: no bake peanut butter marshmallow bars
directions: In the top of a double boiler, put butter, peanut butter and marshmallows.
Heat over hot water until ingredients are melted.

title: vanilla ice cream(made in ice cream freezer.)
directions: Fill ice cream freezer with milk to within 2 to 3 inches of top of freezer container.
Layer crushed ice and salt in the freezer around container.
Crank until real solid or stiff.
Pack with plenty of salt and ice.
Cover ice cream freezer.
See your ice cream freezer instructions for making ice cream.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: cowboy's bean salad
directions: Combine chickpeas, green beans and onion in a large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and beat well to blend flavors.
Add to vegetables and toss lightly.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Makes 10 servings.

title: pineapple fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and butter.
Heat slowly to boiling point. Add pineapple and cook over medium heat to 235° to soft-ball stage, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add lemon juice.
Beat until candy loses gloss.
Turn into buttered pan.
Garnish with pecan halves.

title: waldorf swiss salad
directions: Mix all items lightly.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Put 1 1/2 cups of water in a blender and blend with onion, celery, carrots and garlic.
Place in a cooking pot with the broccoli that has been hand chopped.
Add the McKay's.
Cook over slow heat until vegetables are done.
Thicken with a little flour paste.
Add Velveeta cheese; heat until melted.
Mix well and serve.

title: fried rice with curried meatballs
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water according to package directions until tender.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine ground pork and turkey, the bread crumbs, 1 teaspoon of curry powder and the salt.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Place all ingredients in a casserole and bake covered for 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: madras chicken
directions: Cook and stir bell pepper, onion, garlic and curry powder until vegetables are crisp and tender.
Add chicken; cook and stir 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir in tomatoes, juice, thyme and black pepper.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 5 minutes.
Add Velveeta spread.
Stir until melted.
Serve over cooked rice, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: deluxe potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in water in covered pan until very tender.
Do not drain.
Mash or press potatoes to break up pieces.
Add milk, bouillon cubes and butter.
Continue cooking slowly.
Mix sour cream and flour until smooth.
Add to soup and cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bouillon cubes are dissolved.
Stir in salt and pepper.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Combine 2 cups rhubarb with 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
Cream together 1 1/2 cups sugar and shortening.
Add egg, buttermilk, soda, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Pour in greased and floured long pan.
Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix everything together.
Fill jars not too full.
Cold pack for 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti soup
directions: Saute onion in butter. Bring chicken broth to boil. Add spaghetti and cook until done. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until done.

title: cathedral cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat and beat in egg.
Mix well.
Cool slightly.
In large bowl, combine marshmallows and nuts.
Pour chocolate mixture over the top and mix well.
Divide mixture in half.
Shape each half into a roll approximately 8-inches long.
Wrap roll in a strip of waxed paper which has been heavily sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Chill several hours or overnight; slice to serve.
(Cookies will have a stained glass window appearance.)

title: cream cheese and ham ball
directions: Chop ham in blender and mix all together.

title: creamy orange dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender; blend for about 2 minutes. Pour in greased and floured 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes (gets brown on top).
Cool and chow down.

title: country crust bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar and salt in warm milk; add eggs and oil.
Add 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth. Mix in remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured board.
Knead until smooth and doesn't stick to hands.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Punch down dough; divide in half. Knead and shape into loaves.
Brush loaves with oil.
Let rise until double. Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Brush loaves with butter.

title: basic white sauce
directions: Melt butter in small pan.
Blend in flour and stir constantly about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add milk, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: shrimp in white wine and cream
directions: Saute 1 finely chopped shallot in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add shrimp, pinch of thyme, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 7 minutes.
Warm 2 tablespoons brandy; light it and pour it flaming over the shrimp.

When flame has died, add 3/4 cup white wine. Simmer further 5 minutes, then transfer to heated serving dish. Reduce pan juices by half; add mixture of cream, egg yolks, 1 teaspoon lemon juice and 1 teaspoon each of parsley, chervil and tarragon.
Stir well and pour sauce over shrimp.
Do not let boil.
Serves 4.

title: ham it up hot dish
