directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mr. nik's cheese dip
directions: Combine cheese and tomatoes in microwave-proof bowl.
Heat on High for 4 minutes.
Mix up and heat until melted.
Stir and serve with chips.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
In a pot, combine butter, flour, onion, and seasonings.
Blend in milk gradually; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli and water.
Cook until heated.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; congeal until firm. Mix the cream cheese and Cool Whip together; add pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: crock-pot spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop tomatoes in blender (with peelings on).
Cook in crock-pot on high (covered) for 6 hours.
Then add all other ingredients.
Cook for 2 hours more on high.
Cold pack for 10 minutes or freeze.

title: turkish kofte
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

Form balls (about golf ball size), then flatten. These may be fried, baked in oven (350°) for approximately 3 to 5 minutes per side or barbecued. When cooked, they should resemble small hamburger patties.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Grate cheese; mix together with softened cream cheese, garlic and nuts.
Knead with hands.
Form into rolls and sprinkle with chili powder and cayenne pepper (very small amount of pepper). Put roll in wax paper.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
Slice thin to serve.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: On a large cookie sheet, add all ingredients, making sure the olive oil covers all vegetables. Roast at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: golden grahams s'mores
directions: Grease	rectangular
pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Heat syrup, margarine and morsels to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat;	stir
in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in bowl;
toss until coated.
Fold
in
marshmallows, 1 cup at a time.
Press in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: uncooked chili sauce
directions: Grind and mix well the tomatoes, onions, peppers and salt. Put in bag and drain overnight. Discard liquid.
Add sugar, vinegar and mustard seed.
Mix and can.

title: fat-free strawberry delight
directions: Prepare gelatin according to directions.
Chill until set. Put milk, bowl and beaters in freezer for about 1 hour.
Milk should be icy.
Add half sugar to strawberries.
Beat milk with vanilla and remaining sugar at high speed until stiff peaks form. Quickly whip gelatin until no white streaks remain.
Taste for sweetness and more sugar to taste.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water until tender, about 15 minutes. Drain well.
While pasta is cooking, melt butter in saucepan.
Add half and half and cheeses, a little at a time, over a low heat. Mix gently after each addition.

title: bruschetta with anchovy salad
directions: Prepare the salad.
Coarsely chop the anchovies and place in a mixing bowl.
Add about a 1/4 teaspoon of finely minced garlic, the pimientos, the scallions, 1 tablespoon oil, the lemon juice and parsley.
Reserve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of French fried onions.
Set oven to 350°.
Put in oven to bake for 30 minutes.
After 30 minutes, take out and sprinkle 1 can of onions on top.
Put back in oven and cook 5 minutes.
Take out and serve.

title: oven-baked chicken
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice, garlic salt, paprika and oregano.
Place chickens in baking pan coated with Pam.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour butter sauce over chickens.
Bake at 275° for 3 1/2 hours, turning and brushing occasionally.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple (need to be dry).
Chop finely both onion and pepper.
Mix all together and shape into ball.
Roll in crushed nuts if desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, soup, cheese and 1/2 of onions in 1-quart casserole. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Add rest of onions. Spread on top and cook 5 minutes.

title: crisco cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; set aside.
Beat the 6 egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour in greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix salt, cocoa and soda with flour and add alternately with buttermilk and coffee.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 layers.

title: quick porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix ground meat and rice together.
Shape into meatballs the size of walnuts.
In pressure cooker, heat tomato soup and 1/2 can water until soup is smooth.
Place meatballs into cooker.
Place on lid and pressure cook on 10 pounds pressure for 10 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Let the water, cinnamon, cloves, tea and sugar simmer for 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients and let set for 5 minutes.
Will keep in the refrigerator for quite awhile.

title: cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Drop by teaspoons.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown meat in butter or margarine. Add green pepper and onion. Saute until tender.
Add 4 cups of water and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn chips
directions: Combine cornmeal and salt in mixing bowl.
Pour in 1 cup of boiling water and stir.
Add margarine and stir until melted.
Add another 3/4 cup boiling water and continue stirring.
Drop small spoonfuls of the mixture (about the size of a half dollar) on a greased cookie sheet, then bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes approximately 3 dozen chips.

title: mother's cornbread dressing
directions: Brown onions, peppers, celery and garlic in Crisco in pot.
Add ground gizzard, liver and ground beef.
Cook well.
Add chopped chives, salt, pepper and sage.
Add ground corn bread (recipe follows).
Moisten dressing with butter, water and brandy.
Correct seasoning and add nuts.
Yield:
9 1/2 cups.
Allow 1 cup dressing per pound of fowl.
Stuff loosely into bird to allow for expansion. If you bake separately, place in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice the carrots; cook until slightly crisp.
Drain.
Add the chopped onion and green pepper.
Mix the soup with sugar, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, mustard, oil, salt and pepper. Pour sauce over carrots.
Refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Do not overcook.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Put the milk on to boil in a farina boiler.
Beat the yolks and the sugar together until light, then add them to the boiling milk.
Stir over the fire for two minutes.
Take off, add the vanilla, and put away to cool.

title: mabel's baked beans
directions: In a skillet over low heat brown the ground beef.

On top of the ground beef add, in the following order, the celery, bell peppers and onions and saute (stir the ground beef from underneath, leaving the chopped vegetables on top to ensure that neither the ground beef nor the vegetables are overcooked). Remove from heat and drain well (all fat must be drained).

title: rolled cookies
directions: Combine egg, orange juice and butter.
Slowly add cake mix.
If too stiff, add more orange juice concentrate.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill.
Roll about 1/8-inch thick and bake on greased cookie sheets for 5 to 8 minutes at 325°.
(Can also use chocolate mix and Kahlua.)

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine and bake until hot.
Serve with bread cubes or potato chips.

title: dunking platters(cookies)
directions: Blend together thoroughly the melted butter and sugars in large saucepan.
Add and beat in eggs and vanilla; mix in oats and cereal.
Add flour, soda and baking powder; mix.
Drop by tablespoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: chicken and green bean stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Combine lemon juice, garlic and 1 tablespoon soy sauce in a bowl.
Add chicken and toss.
Trim beans and cook in boiling salted water until tender or about 8 minutes. Drain.
Combine remaining 1 tablespoon soy sauce, broth and cornstarch.
Heat oil in large frying pan or wok.
Remove chicken from marinade and add to hot pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until chicken is just done, about 5 minutes.
Push chicken to one side and stir stock mixture into pan drippings.
Stir chicken into sauce and add beans.
Cook until beans are heated through, about 1 minute.
Sprinkle with peanuts and serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease a pan.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in eggs and buttermilk.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: margie's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and flour; mix until sugar is dissolved well.
Add butter, vanilla and syrup; mix.
Add pecans.
Bake in 300° oven about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: pralines
directions: Cook and
stir over low heat until sugar dissolves; add nuts. Boil
slowly;
stir
until	soft ball stage is reached. Remove from
heat; beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop from spoon onto double thick wax paper about 4 inches apart.

title: cranberry orange mold
directions: Wash and dry cranberries.
Peel oranges and save peel.
Put cranberries and peel from one orange in food processor.
Process until finely chopped.
Dice orange pulp and add to cranberries with sugar.
Process just until combined.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Let cool.
Add cranberry-orange mixture and pour into oiled mold.
Chill until firm.

title: stuffed banana pepper
directions: Mixed above ingredients together to form a pastry.
Split peppers, remove seeds.
Stuff with American or Velveeta cheese. Roll in pastry.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Set this aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, line with wax paper and grease wax paper.
Spread pumpkin mixture in pan.
Top with walnut pieces.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on kitchen towel sprinkled with powdered sugar. Remove wax paper and roll towel and cake up jelly roll fashion. Cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Unroll and spread cake surface with mixture of confectioners sugar, cream cheese, margarine and vanilla. Reroll and chill.

title: onion-cheese supper bread
directions: Cook onion in small amount of oil until just tender.
Combine egg and milk.
Add Bisquick mix, onion, 1/2 the cheese and the parsley.
Spread dough in greased 8-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Drizzle margarine over top. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: big bean pot
directions: Saute bacon and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° uncovered for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Beat eggs and sugar. Add other ingredients.
Bake in buttered baking dish 1 hour at 325°.

title: wyatt's cafeteria eggplant casserole
directions: Soak peeled eggplant overnight in salt water in refrigerator. Soak bread in milk next morning.
Saute onion, celery and green peppers in oleo until tender.
Boil eggplant until tender. Drain.
Mix eggplant and vegetables together.
Add eggs, salt, pepper, sage and pimento.
Blend.
Cook in greased casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with cheese.

title: savory eggs
directions: Put cheese on bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Put butter around on cheese.
Combine half and half, salt, pepper, mustard and parsley.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture over cheese and butter. Add eggs and the rest of the half and half mixture by spoon over eggs.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix
Cool Whip and dry jello together with mixer.
Keep mixing cottage cheese and pineapple together.
Add marshmallows.
Chill.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into one-half inch slices.
Salt each piece, stack and let stand one hour while sauce is cooking.
Juice will come from eggplant in this manner.

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat Dream Whip.
Add pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Mix well. Put in freezer for 30 minutes.
Then put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: diabetic sweet potato and chunky apple pie
directions: Scrub and prick sweet potatoes; microwave for 5 minutes on High power.
Hold under cold water to peel.
Cut into chunks and add to bowl of food processor fitted with steel blade.
Process about 3 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil together until foamy.
Beat in sugar. Combine soda, salt, cinnamon and flour.
Stir into egg mixture. Add vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or Cream Cheese Icing.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick with uncooked sausage.
Add cheese (shredded). Knead with hands.
Roll into bite size pieces.
Place onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
Use spatula to lift off cookie sheet.

title: coca-cola frosting
directions: In a double boiler, combine all ingredients.
Cook over rapid boiling water, beating with rotary beater or electric mixer until stands in peaks.
Remove from heat and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: potato soup(girl scout camp recipe)
directions: Bring water and salt to boil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: frittata o'brien
directions: Melt butter in an 8 inch iron skillet over medium heat.
Add potatoes and cook until lightly browned, stirring occasionally, about 5 to 7 minutes.
In a small bowl, beat together eggs, water, and salt and pour over potatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat until eggs are almost set, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place under broiler about 6 inches from heat until eggs are completely set and cheese is melted, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Cut into serving pieces.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook hen in large stock pot with about 3 quarts water and 1/2 stick margarine.
Add more water as needed.
When chicken is getting tender and liquid has reduced to about half, add the two cans of broth.
Bring back to a boil and cook about 15 minutes longer.
Remove cooked chicken (reserving broth).
Stir in cream of chicken soup until well blended.
Debone chicken and set aside. Place 2 tablespoons margarine in skillet, add onions and celery, saute.
While chicken cooks make cornbread.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press dinner rolls into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook and drain sausage.
Crumble hash browns; cook in bacon grease.
Drain well.
Put a layer of sausage, hash browns and 1 cup cheese.
Beat together the eggs and milk; pour into pan.
Add remaining cup of cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: fido's fabulous people crackers
directions: You will also need large bowl, cookie sheet, rolling pin, cutting board, spatula and cookie cutters.

title: red chicken stew
directions: Boil fryer and debone.
Fry fatback.
Cook onions in fatback drippings.
Pour in tomato sauce.
Add chicken broth, salt and pepper to taste.
Add dash of Texas Pete to taste.
Add sugar to taste.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
If more broth is needed, add canned broth.

title: delicious impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 or 10 inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon evenly over bottom of pie plate.
Place remaining ingredients in blender or food processor.
Blend well; pour into pie plate.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Blend together in food processor. Store in covered jar in refrigerator. Makes 1 (15 ounce) can.

title: speedy tuna casserole
directions: Crush potato chips.
Mix all ingredients; salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
(Kids love it!)

title: herbed potatoes
directions: Thinly slice potatoes and onion.
Put half of the potatoes and half of the onion.
Sprinkle with half of the seasoning.
Drizzle with half of the butter.
Repeat the steps in a casserole dish. Cover with foil and bake on 425° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 10 to 20 minutes more or until the potatoes are tender.

title: julia's easy hollandaise sauce
directions: Bring lemon juice and water to the simmer; add salt.
In separate saucepan, beat egg and yolks with wire whip for about 1 minute.
Set yolk mixture over low heat and whisk in hot lemon juice by driblets.
Slowly whisk until forms a foamy mass; remove from heat.
Immediately beat in warm melted margarine by driblets to make a thick, creamy, light yellow sauce.

title: 30 minute spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic in hot Wesson until soft. Add meat. Stir and cook until meat loses red color. Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, basil, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes. Pour over hot cooked spaghetti.

title: susie's b.b.q.
directions: Cook in crock pot on low for 8 hours or high 4 hours. Debone and shred, remove bay leaves. Add 1 to 2 bottles Hickory Smoke BBQ sauce. Extra can be frozen.

title: m. e.'s lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles (directions on box).
Mix oregano with Prego sauce.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Line noodles in baking dish the long way.
Spread cottage cheese over noodles, covering them.
Add Mozzarella cheese and Prego sauce.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.
Let stand 10 minutes after taking from oven.
Lasagna will be very stringy, so let stand.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well with electric mixer.
Store in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter roundups(cookies)
directions: Beat shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix in peanut butter.
Sift flour, salt and soda; stir into other mixture.
Stir in oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cinnamon baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in oven dish.
Cook for 30 minutes at 400°.
(You may want to shorten or lengthen the time according to your own preference.)

title: oliebollen
directions: Mix flour and salt and make a hole in the middle.
Place the egg in the hole.
Heat milk to lukewarm and mix yeast with part of the milk to dissolve it.
Place the dissolved yeast mixture in the middle of the flour with the rest of the milk.
Start stirring from the middle and go outwards.
Add washed and strained raisins. Put a tea towel over the dough and let rise for about an hour. Drop batter by spoons into hot oil and fry until golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Combine milk, water and pudding mix in bowl. Mix well. Chill until thick. Fold in whipped topping. Alternate layers pudding mix, pound cake and strawberries in glass bowl. Chill and serve.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and cook 10 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking. Pour into pint jars and seal. Place in pressure canner for 15 minutes at 10 lb. pressure. Pressure quarts for 20 minutes at 10 lb. pressure. Makes 7 pints.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown sausage; crumble in small pieces until done.
Drain. Place back in clean pan.
Add all cans of soup.
Simmer until ready to serve.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple and lemon juice.
Chop cranberries and orange together in food chopper.
Discard juice.
Add all ingredients to Jell-O mixture and mix well.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, baking powder and salt in bowl; mix well. Add onion (optional); mix well. Stir in egg. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. Deep-fry in hot oil until brown. Taste best when fried in oil used to fry fish.

title: aunt nell's cake(pound cake)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy and smooth (minimum of 7 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add salt.
Thoroughly mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake in a treated Bundt pan 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
Bake at 325°.

title: chocolate sour cream cake
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients together.
Mix well.
Combine water, soda and vanilla.
Pour over batter, mixing well.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread 2 packages of cream cheese on bottom of a pie plate. Layer chili with beans on top of cream cheese and shredded Monterey Jack cheese on top of chili.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Dip with tortilla chips!

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until done.
Pour powdered sugar icing over top.

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cut into squares and serve.

title: chocolate chip-banana muffins
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in bananas.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.
Beat until blended.
Stir in mini morsels.
Spray Pam on the bottom of each cup of a muffin tin.
Pour in batter until 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 18 muffins.

title: shrimp bisque(serves 4 to 6.)
directions: Grind shrimp in blender or food processor.
Combine margarine and flour in saucepan.
Add milk and salt.
Stir until thickened. Add lemon juice, Tabasco, white pepper and shrimp.
Add sherry to suit your taste.
Serve hot with lemon slices.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Drain cherries; set aside.
Combine together all of the above ingredients, except cherries and graham crackers; refrigerate for 1 hour.
Use 1 teaspoon of dough around each cherry.
Roll in hand until cherry is covered.
Roll in crushed graham crackers. Refrigerate until served.

title: kay's black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at the time and vanilla.
Reserve 1/4 to 1/2 cup flour to flour nuts.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Start and end with flour. Fold in nuts.

title: chocolate filled bon-bons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco, sugar, add eggs, vanilla and almond extract, beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Mix. Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Press each ball around kiss so it is completely enclosed like a chocolate covered cherry. Bake 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool on wire racks. Frost or decorate as desired.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen cookies.

title: cream cheese dip(for fresh fruit)
directions: Soften the 8 ounces of cream cheese (or 3 ounces, depending on how much fruit you have).
Mix with a beater.
Beat in pineapple juice and confectioners sugar until sweet.
Add just enough juice, until it is the thickness you want.
Refrigerate.
Very fast and delicious with fresh fruit.

title: chocolate butter cream frosting
directions: Cream together adding milk slowly.
You may need a little more milk as you mix them together.
Spread over cool cake.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Remove ends and strings from pea pods.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Combine chicken with 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 2 teaspoons sherry.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for at least 30 minutes.
Combine remaining soy sauce, broth, cornstarch and sugar in covered jar.
Shake and set aside.
Combine mushrooms, pea pods and 1 teaspoon oil.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add green onions and water chestnuts.
Stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Remove vegetables. Combine marinated chicken with 1 teaspoon oil in skillet and spread in single layer.
Cook over medium heat until moisture evaporates and chicken cubes begin to brown.
Turn to brown evenly.
Shake up broth mixture and stir into the chicken.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens.
Return vegetables to pan.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Stir in nuts at last minute.
Serves 4. Contains 270 calories.

title: eggs avocado
directions: Mash the pulp from the avocado.
Mix with the lemon juice, garlic juice, salt and pepper to taste, mustard, melted butter and vinegar.
Cut the hard-boiled eggs in half and remove yolks.
Put yolks through sieve and add to avocado mix.
Taste for seasoning and fill egg whites.

title: chili chicken
directions: Lightly salt chicken, coat with flour and fry until cooked. Boil first four (4) ingredients until mixture just thickens.
Add green onions after heat has been turned off.
Either dip chicken in sauce or pour sauce on chicken and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk in an electric skillet.
Set temperature at 275° to 280°.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch buttered pan. Let set.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water until firm, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water to stop cooking process. Drain well.
Add the vegetables and seasonings.
Toss several times.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve cold.
Delicious.

title: harvest potatoes with herbs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In small bowl, combine seasoning.
Place 2 tablespoons melted butter in 10-inch nonstick skillet.
(If handles are not ovenproof, wrap with foil.)
Arrange 1/3 of the potato slices into a circular pattern in skillet.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon seasonings, 4 teaspoons butter and 1 tablespoon onion. Repeat layers twice.
Cover tightly with foil.
Press layers down. Bake 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust: Mix cookie mix according to package directions. Spread cookie mix on a lightly greased pizza pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°. Divide popcorn into two ungreased cake pans. Heat sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt, stirring occasionally until bubbly around the edges. Cook on medium heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in Soda. Pour on popcorn. Stir until coated.	Bake 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes.	Can add peanuts if desired.

title: avocado salad dressing
directions: Mash avocado with fork.
Pour in Wesson oil and garlic powder. Dice tomatoes, lettuce and celery; add onion.
Mix together. Add a little salt and pepper.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Simmer melted margarine and brown sugar for 8 to 10 minutes. Add salt, vanilla and milk and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add mixture to powdered sugar.
Beat until cool.
Spread on cake.
You can heat this frosting in microwave until warm.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Combine sugar, cream of tartar, salt and water in a small saucepan.
Bring to boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring to 240° on candy thermometer or until a soft ball forms in cold water.
Set syrup aside.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Add salt to taste. Crumble 1 sleeve of crackers and put on top.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: cherry cake
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add flour and baking powder.
Save 1 cup of dough.
Grease an 11 x 16 x 1-inch pan.
Spread dough. Add pie filling.
Pour here and there over dough.
Take reserved cup of dough and spoon over filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, margarine and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven and press firmly into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cool.
Save 1/4 cup crumbs for top.

title: leelanau country innkeeper's caramel pecan pie
directions: On a lightly floured surface, roll pastry to a 12-inch circle. Place in a 9-inch plate.
Turn under edge; flute.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crusts.
Bake at 275° approximately 1 hour, until lightly browned.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Dissolve
bouillon
in
water.
Cook onion in butter or margarine
until
tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk
and bouillon gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add crabmeat and heat, but do not boil.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash and onion; mix other ingredients well and mix with squash.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° about 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Fry bacon.
In a separate pan, brown garlic with olive oil on low heat.
Add bacon, basil and wine to garlic mixture when garlic is lightly browned.
In another large serving bowl, add beaten eggs, cheese, parsley and salt and pepper.
Cook spaghetti; drain and put on top of egg mixture.
Stir well.
Add garlic mixture. Serves 4.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and process until blended.

title: ship wreck casserole
directions: Saute beef in pan until it loses red color. In a 2 qt. casserole, place sliced potatoes on bottom, place onions over these. Add can of kidney beans and broth. Next add ground beef and then empty tomato
soup over all. Lightly salt and pepper each layer.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop from a spoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: cold chicken rice salad
directions: Cook together rice and bouillon.
Add oil and soy sauce.
Stir and chill.
Just before serving or a few hours earlier, add 2 cups chicken, bean sprouts, mushrooms, onions, pimientos.
Stir together and serve.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese and melt in microwave, stirring every minute.
Add Ro-Tel and chili; heat.
Serve warm with corn or tortilla chips or use as a sauce over Mexican food.

title: ava's potato salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, parsley, onion, salt and pepper.
In a bowl (glass is beautiful) layer the warm potato slices (with skins on) and the dressing.
Cover and let stand at room temperature, at least 30 minutes.
Just before serving, add beans, ham, lettuce and radishes.
Toss and serve.

title: jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, beat butter and sugars until light and fluffy; add egg. Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture. Stir in M&M's baking bits, raisins and nuts. Drop rounded tablespoon of dough (1 1/2-inch ball) about 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheets. Bake 13 to 15 minutes. Cool 2 to 3 minutes on cookie sheets before transferring to wire racks to cool thoroughly. Store in tight container. Makes about 32 cookies.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef, celery, onion and green pepper in oil. Mix cornstarch, water, bouillon cube, soy sauce and salt.
Add to beef and vegetable mixture.
Cook over medium heat until clear and thickened.
Add cabbage and cook until done.
Just before serving, add bean sprouts, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Serve on cooked rice.

title: garlic bread pape'
directions: Heat garlic butter.
Spoon on bread, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place under broiler for 1 to 2 minutes.
Turn bread and repeat on other side.
Watch carefully.
Burns easily.

title: lithuanian borsch(cold soup)
directions: Mix
diced
beets, cucumbers and onions with sour cream in large
bowl.
Stir	until
sour
cream is blended.	Add reserved beet
juice.
Stir	until beet juice and sour cream are blended. Add
milk
to
fill
bowl.	Stir.
Add chopped eggs. Salt to taste.
Add ice cubes to chill (may remove most of the ice cubes when soup is cold.) Time of preparation: 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and confectioners sugar together. Add melted butter.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cream cheese; add eggs and sugar.
Put mixture on top of crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Spread can of blueberry pie filling on top of cream cheese layer.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate.

title: jap chae(potato noodle with mixed vegetables)
directions: Cut in half or 1/4 the cooked noodles; stir-fry.
Add soy sauce, sugar, black pepper, toasted sesame seed, chopped garlic, sliced scallions.

title: company pancakes and homemade syrup
directions: Add poppy seeds to your batter.
Bring water and sugar to a simmer and remove from heat.
Quickly stir in butter and almond extract.
Pour syrup over hot pancakes.
Experiment with different extracts in your syrup and different additives to your pancakes.

title: 7-layer casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place ingredients in layers in a 2-quart baking dish with tight fitting lid.
Place rice and corn in the dish; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce and 1/2 can water over this layer.
Add onion, green pepper and hamburger, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Pour can of tomato sauce and 1/4 can of water over all.
Cover meat with 4 strips of bacon.
Cover dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt and spice together; pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Drizzle melted butter over mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Serve with whipped topping.

title: white easter soup
directions: Bring water, kielbasa, onion, garlic, peppercorns and bay leaf to boil; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Combine about 1 tablespoon of cream with flour, then add this mixture to remaining cream. Stir into soup.
Cook over very low heat until slightly thickened. Add vinegar to taste.
Serve garnished with hard-cooked eggs. Serves 8.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust. Cover with top crust; crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: deep dish vegetable pie
directions: Saute ingredients in 1/4 cup butter and drain.
Toss in 1 cup sliced or cubed tomato.
Pour in shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread mix according to directions.
Cool.
Crumble into a large bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Cool.
Crumble into large bowl with corn bread.
Add other ingredients and toss or mix thoroughly with a light hand.
Refrigerate.
Will keep several days.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and save out 1 cup for top.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put in regular cake pan.
Put the cup of crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: quick baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over margarine.
Put potatoes in baking dish, cut side down. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Potatoes will be coated with margarine and cheese.

title: cherry jello surprise
directions: Pour 1 1/4 cups boiling water on cherry jello in large bowl. Stir in cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate until firm.
Pour 1 cup boiling water on orange jello in a separate bowl.
Stir in pineapple and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Mix Cool Whip with pineapple/orange jello mixture.
Pour over cherry mixture; refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken
directions: Melt shortening and butter in cake pan on burner.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and flour over chicken.
Place chicken in pan, turning pieces over after baking for 30 minutes.
Bake in 425° oven for 30 minutes on each side.

title: quick tartar sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed.
Chill.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package directions and drain. In a large skillet, heat butter and olive oil.
Add shrimp and garlic; cook until shrimp are opaque.
Combine cooked spaghetti, shrimp mixture, cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss until well mixed.

title: jackie's baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together in a long rectangular pan or casserole dish.
Bake uncovered approximately 60 to 90 minutes, until thick and bubbly.
Remove from oven.
Let cool down slightly to set, then serve.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup pecans.
Mix well and shape into 2 balls.
Coat each with 1/4 cup pecans.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: In a small saucepan, melt chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk; set aside.
In large bowl of electric mixer, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Gradually blend in chocolate mixture; pour into unbaked pie shell.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: In large skillet, melt butter and stir-fry onions and carrots until tender (not browned).
Set aside.
In small skillet, melt butter.
Stir-fry mushrooms until tender.
Let saute in butter while preparing remainder of ingredients.
In large (6-quart or more) saucepan, stir together rice, chicken, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots and bean sprouts (if desired).
Add soy sauce and stir until rice has a light brown color.
Add remainder of ingredients (onions, carrots and mushrooms).
Stir.

title: shrimp boursin
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
While it is cooking, combine butter and lemon juice in a large skillet and heat.
Add shrimp and garlic powder and saute until shrimp is pink.
Lower heat and add Boursin Cheese, breaking it up.
As it warms, it makes the sauce.
Pour over drained pasta.
Toss gently. Add tomato as garnish.

title: aunt shirlee's easy brownies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in bowl.
Add cocoa; add sugar in the large bowl.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well with each egg addition.
Add flour; stir well.
Add nuts and put in pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with or without icing.

title: brie torte
directions: Save out a few orange slices for garnish; chop up the rest in food processor. Mix chopped orange, cream cheese and orange extract together well. Set aside 2/3 of this mix to be used later. Split the Brie into 2 layers, spread the orange mix as in "icing" between the layers; spread the ground nuts on the "icing", put layers together. Use the 2/3 previously set aside to "ice" the Brie which has been filled. Decorate with orange slices and nasturtium leaves or blossoms.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets and reserve the liquid.
In a pan, combine the liquid, sugar, vinegar and cloves.
Bring to a simmer and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour liquid over beets.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Press rolls onto buttered pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let rolls cool.
Beat cream cheese, Miracle Whip and minced onion until well blended.
Spread cream cheese mixture onto cooled rolls.
Cut up your choice of veggies into small pieces and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix all together and put a layer of Vanilla Wafers and a layer of filling.

title: stuffed crab rollswarren, texas
directions: Use diced, cooked shrimp and crab meat.
Put Italian bread crumbs, red pepper, garlic, salt and pepper.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Cook vegetables halfway.
Place in
casserole and cover with any kind cheese.
Mix crackers with oleo and
put
on top of mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Then form into balls.
Set aside on wax paper.
Next step melt wax and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Last step, dip balls into melted chocolate with a toothpick.
Set them back on wax paper for cooling.
Also if you don't like chocolate do first 3 ingredients and roll balls up in coconut.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together the brown sugar and butter.
Beat in eggs.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: charlie's pan-fried rainbow trout with kamloop sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat over hot water. Serve warm over pan-fried trout or use as a side dish instead of tartar sauce.

title: "pizza"-dillas
directions: Butter one side of a flour tortilla.
Place in a frying pan over medium-high heat, buttered side down.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and pepperoni slices that have been sliced thinly again into small strips.
Sprinkle with another thin layer of cheese. Top with another flour tortilla, buttered side up.
Heat on both sides until crisp and lightly browned.
Cut into pizza style slices.
Serve warm.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Place chicken in 9 x 12 baking dish. Cover with sauce and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Can be frozen.

title: cinnamon swirl loaves
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
In saucepan, heat milk, water and butter until warm (120° to 130°).
Butter does not need to melt.
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs; blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a firm dough. Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic, 5 to 8 minutes. Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place, about 1 hour.

title: easy cucumber relish
directions: Drain cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Add salt.
Place in large saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer 20 minutes.
Pack into hot, sterilized jars and seal. Makes 10 to 12 pints.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the juice in a small pan.
Set pineapple aside.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/3 cups.
Bring to a boil and pour over gelatin in a bowl; stir thoroughly.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Whip cream and gradually beat in sugar. Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese.
Blend well.
Chill in 1 1/2-quart bowl for 3 hours or overnight.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken broth and milk.
Bring to a boil until thickened.
Add mushrooms, pimento, salt and pepper, bell pepper and 1 cup chicken.
Simmer over low heat for about 5 minutes. Serve over toast, biscuits or plain bread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
Cut cheese into cubes.
Crush crackers.
Drain broccoli and put into casserole.
Place cheese on top and add crackers.
Pour butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until heated through and crunchy on top.

title: danish shrimp salad sandwich
directions: Cut cucumbers in half, lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds; shred finely.
Drain well in colander and chill.
Drain shrimp of excess moisture.
Combine sour cream, lemon peel, juice, onions, dill and garlic.
Toss lightly with shrimp.
Fold in almonds.
Butter the bread.
Arrange shredded cucumber over each slice.
Top with shrimp salad mixture.

title: cheesy chicken (microwave)
directions: Place 1 Tbsp. butter in an 11x7 microwaveable dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and pepper.
Dip chicken in remaining butter, then spread with sour cream.
Roll in crumbs.
Place in prepared dish. Cover loosely and microwave on high for 6-7 minutes, or until juices run clear.
Let stand for 5-10 minutes before serving.

title: one-step yeast rolls
directions: Soften Crisco in hot water; add sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water with a tablespoon of sugar.
Add egg; mix well all together and add flour.
Mix well with fork.
Place in refrigerator to chill for several hours (best overnight).

Make rolls out several hours before baking (or enough time to double in bulk). Cut to make Parker House shape or make cloverleaf in muffin tins. Bake at 350° to 375° for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: oil cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine liquids.
Add liquids to dry.
Beat 5 minutes. Bake in prepared 8-inch square pan for 35 minutes.

title: mohle - all-purpose sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients until thick.
Serve with any meat or fish as sauce, baste or marinade.
Serve on rice also.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Dump pie filling and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with dry cake mix and pecans.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Delicious warm with vanilla ice cream!

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 325°
for approximately one hour until cake springs back to touch.

title: sweet potatoes pie
directions: Mix the ingredients together and beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until firm around sides, about 45 minutes.

title: fanny's fantastic bread
directions: Cut bread crosswise like a pineapple (about 1 inch cuts) just down to the bottom crust.
Mix cheese with mushrooms and stuff into the cuts.
Place on a large sheet of heavy aluminum foil. (May do this much the night before.
Wrap and refrigerate.)

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut the cabbage up into small chunks. Cook in water and a little salt until barely tender. Drain. Spread in buttered casserole, about 9 x 12-inches, about 1-inch deep.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Layer in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Mix soup and can of milk or sour cream together.
Place ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Place soup mixture in bottom of dish, then tortillas, with a layer of chicken, onion, chiles and cheese.
Put soup over top and start layers over.
Cover with foil.

title: peanut butter chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, shortening and peanut butter in one bowl.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and chocolate chips in another bowl.
Mix together well.
Bake 10 minutes.
If you did not use chocolate chips, immediately put kiss in middle of cookies.
Let melt, then enjoy.

title: marmalade coffee cake
directions: Spread marmalade in bottom of greased 12-cup Bundt pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Separate biscuits; dip in butter and dredge in sugar mixture.
Stand each biscuit on edge around pan, spacing evenly. Drizzle with remaining butter and top with remaining sugar mixture.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Saute onions and celery in butter. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Combine all ingredients, except spaghetti and cheese.
Place in layers, beginning with spaghetti on bottom, then cheese, then sauce.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and egg together.
Combine flour, sugar and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form dough into 2 (1-inch) rolls.
Wrap in plastic and chill at least 2 to 3 hours.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 375°
for 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 6 dozen nutritious delicious cookies.
Great for school lunch boxes.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Combine sugar and water, stir; add yeast, stir.
Add oil, stir. Add beaten egg, stir.
Mix with flour.
Cover and let rise 1 hour. Drop by spoon into small bowl of flour, form into biscuit.
Put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cranberry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, 3/4 cup of sugar and butter.
Mix until crumbly; reserve 1 1/2 cups of mixture. Press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: potato rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over 1/2 cup of the very warm water in a small bowl.
Stir gently to dissolve the yeast.
Let stand until bubbly, about 10 minutes.
(It "proofs" better with a little bit of sugar added to it.)

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Butter well a 1-quart casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour and mix well.
Stir in water and then milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until white sauce thickens.
Flake crabmeat.
Add crabmeat, celery, onion, pimento, eggs and salt to sauce, then add almonds.
Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Brown pork chops slightly in a frying pan.
In a casserole, place a layer of sliced potatoes and a layer of sliced onion; repeat layers.
Pour undiluted cream of mushroom soup over layers. Place chops on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Line a 10 x 15-inch baking pan with tortillas. Brown meat and onion. Drain. Spread over tortillas. Add beans and cubed cheese. Cut remaining tortillas in strips. Arrange over casserole.
Mix soup and Ro-Tel (cut up tomatoes).
Spread over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 275°.
Reduce to 350° and bake another 30 minutes.

title: gilda's mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix flour, milk and mayo thoroughly. Spoon into well-greased muffin pan and bake in preheated 350° oven until begins to brown on top. Serve with butter and impress your guest. Makes 6. Double for dozen.

title: chicken with salami
directions: Makes 2 servings.
Heat frying pan.
Add olive oil, then chicken.
Add salt and pepper to chicken.
Once chicken gets whiteish, turn over and add onions, salami and mushrooms.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add garlic, butter and parsley; stir constantly.
Once chicken is firm, this dish is complete.
Serve over pasta or rice.

title: egg stuffed tomatoes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients except tomatoes.
Heat skillet to moderate heat and add 2 tablespoons of unsalted butter. Cook eggs until they are done, but not dry.
Stuff tomatoes with eggs and garnish with chopped chives.

title: microwave roux
directions: Pour into a large bowl.
Cook on High for 8 minutes and stir. Cook again on High 4 minutes and stir.
Then 1 minute on High and stir.
Makes 1 pint of roux.

title: crab snacks
directions: Combine
spread,
margarine
and mayonnaise.
Mix well. Add crab meat.	Spread on each 1/2 muffin.
Broil 3 minutes or until brown.

title: beef and rice skillet fiesta
directions: Brown meat quickly in oil in skillet, leaving meat in coarse chunks.
Add onion; cook over medium heat until onion is tender. Add seasoning, tomatoes, corn and bouillon.
Bring to a boil. Stir in green pepper; boil again.
Stir in rice; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
(Use the rice straight from the box.)

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and reserve juice from all the fruits except the cherries.
Cook 3 cups juice in vanilla pudding until it is clear and thick.
Cool.
Pour over fruit.
Set overnight in refrigerator.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Mix oleo and garlic powder. Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet. Serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: good morning casserole
directions: About 50 minutes before serving, cook sausage until well browned; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice bread into 1/2-inch diagonal slices.
Line bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with bread, overlapping slices, if necessary.
Spoon 1/2 of sausage on top of bread.

title: crab dip
directions: Heat soup, do not boil, thoroughly.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water just before adding the hot soup.
Let cool.
Mix together with the other ingredients.
Mold and refrigerate.

title: banana split(no baking)
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with oleo or butter as if you were making a cracker crumb crust.

Layer bottom of a 13 x 13-inch pan. Drain the pineapple and spread over the crumb mixture. Beat the eggs, 1 stick oleo and confectioners sugar together 15 minutes so that it will be stiff and well mixed.
Pour over pineapple. Slice the bananas lengthwise and cover sugar mixture.
Cover bananas with the Cool Whip and sprinkle on chopped nuts. "Voila."

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together, roll in cabbage leaf. Mix Sauerkraut and diced onions, place in large kettle, add cabbage rolls, cook on top of stove 3 hours. Freezes well.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Cook first three ingredients over low heat, while stirring, until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and stir.
Press into 9-inch pie pan, bottom and sides.

title: carraway's breakfast casserole
directions: Layer greased large casserole dish with half of the toast cubes, sausage and cheese; repeat.
Beat eggs; add salt, pepper and milk. Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight covered with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Add crushed cornflakes and bake 25 to 30 minutes more.

title: diet chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot or on stove until tender.

title: red hot salad
directions: Melt red hots in water for jello (2 cups water); bring to a boil.
Add jello; let cool.
Add applesauce.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix zucchini, sugar and egg; blend in oil.
Stir together flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, nutmeg and baking powder.
Add lemon peel or juice.
Blend in nuts (optional).
Bake at 300° for 1 hour (check after 50 minutes or so).
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place sliced peaches in a saucepan.
Add nutmeg and cinnamon and heat.
Grease casserole lightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients all together in pie pan (casserole).
Press ingredients to bottom of pan after mixing.
Pour hot fruit over mixture and bake in hot oven (350°).
Crust will rise over peaches and brown.
Remove from oven.
Serve hot.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup coconut, 2 cups of the milk and the cornstarch in blender.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add remaining coconut and vanilla. Allow to completely cool.
Place 2 tablespoons of reserved coconut in baking pan and bake at 350°, tossing slightly to brown.
Put the cooled coconut/milk mixture in baked pie shell. Prepare topping as directed on package.
After stiff peaks form, add sugar substitute and mix well.
Spread on top of coconut pie, sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Keep refrigerated.
Yield: 8 servings, calories per serving 102, not including pie crust calories.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a separate pan, cook linguini, accordingly and drain.

title: easy crany jelly
directions: Combine Sure-Jell and juice in kettle.
Cook rapidly and stir 5 minutes until bubbles form around the edge.
Do not boil.
However if you want it a little solid, boil it for a very little time.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix corn oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour and cinnamon.
Blend in apples and pecans.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked eggplants
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients except parsley. Chill.
Mold into desired shape. Garnish with lots of parsley. Serve with Ritz crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: spinach dip and hawaiian bread
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Cut out middle of loaf of Hawaiian bread and spoon in mixture.
To serve, slice bread and spread with mixture.
Yummy!

title: garlic broiled lobster tails
directions: Drop lobster tails into boiling salted water and cook for 10 minutes.
Remove from water and cool.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a small saucepan and keep warm.
Trim the shell and loosen the lobster meat from shell.
Place in a shallow pan and baste with the butter mixture.
Broil until brown, basting frequently.
Serve immediately.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut wing tips off.
Discard.
Cut each wing in half.
Arrange wings on broiler pan rack.
Broil 6 inches from heat until browned, turning occasionally (25 to 30 minutes).
Heat butter, Tabasco and vinegar in small pan.
When wings are browned, place on serving tray, alternating with celery sticks.
Drizzle butter mixture over wing sections only.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool, peel and shred or mash coarsely. Over low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter, stirring until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion and seasoning.
Fold in potatoes.

title: easy corn fritters
directions: Stir baking powder into flour, add remaining ingredients. Heat frypan to 350°.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Turn once.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Drain hominy and place in a greased casserole dish.
Add pimento and onion.
Make a cheese sauce with remaining items. Pour over hominy.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: posole(traditional mexican christmas eve supper)
directions: Boil meat with spices, chili and onion until very tender. Cool.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove solidified fat.
Chop pork in bite size.
Return to liquid.
Add drained hominy.
Bring to boil.
Reduce to simmer.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve in bowls. Serve with condiments as desired (finely chopped green onion, sliced radishes, chopped lettuce, lime squeezed over, warm tortillas, corn or flour).
Even better a day or two later.

title: creamy fettuccine alfredo
directions: In large saucepan, stir together cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, margarine and milk over low heat until smooth.
Add fettuccine. Toss lightly.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello with boiling water, stirring until dissolved. Then add strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Place in shallow serving dish or individual serving glasses.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: corned beef hash
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine.
Stir in potatoes, meat, onion, parsley, Worcestershire sauce and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Spread evenly into skillet.
Cook over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until browned on bottom, turning occasionally.
Stir in milk, if desired, and heat through.
Serves four.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce with sugar, vinegar and mustard and stir until sugar dissolves.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Put into baking dish.
Add remaining tomato sauce on top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 400°.

title: crock-pot zesty roast
directions: Trim most of the fat off roast.
Place in crock-pot and sprinkle salad dressing mix over the roast.
Next, sprinkle gravy mix.
Do not add any water.
Cook on low heat for 6 to 8 hours. Makes own gravy.
Turn roast over during last hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Make white sauce out of the first 5 ingredients.
Put half the potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with half the onion and half the white sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Uncover; continue baking until top is browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach rice salad
directions: Cook rice. Cool slightly. Add dressing, soy sauce and sugar; cover and chill. Before serving, add spinach, celery, green onions and crumbled bacon.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Add pecans and bananas.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 2 loaf pans.
Can be frozen.

title: connie's shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire, soy sauce and grated onion.
Blend well.
Spread thin layer on a serving platter.
Chill two or more hours.
Spread chili sauce on top evenly.
Top with washed, drained shrimp. Garnish with fresh parsley.
Serve with Wheat Thins crackers.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup of sugar and flour.
Stir in egg yolks and milk.
Cook slowly over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Pour custard over layers.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut bacon slab in 1/3 sections.
Wrap water chestnuts with a bacon section.
Secure with a toothpick. Bake until crisp.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour over crisp bacon rolls.
Bake 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes about 25 hors d'oeuvres.

title: bacon wrapped fried oysters
directions: Combine eggs and milk in a shallow dish.
Dip oysters in mixture, then in cracker meal.
Repeat process.
Wrap oysters in bacon, secured by a toothpick.
Fry in shallow hot oil until golden.
May also be placed under the broiler.

title: mock filet mignon
directions: Shape into 2-inch balls.
Brown, then place into baking pan.

title: grandma emma's banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening; add eggs, mix together until smooth.
Add mashed bananas and baking soda.
Mix well; add flour stirring well; stir in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Insert knife in center; done when knife comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs and nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Top with crumbs, then nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in large bowl; cut in shortening.
Add milk and knead until smooth.
Roll and cut into 3-inch squares.
Deep fat fry in 1/2-inch oil at 375° until golden brown on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Best served hot with honey.
Can be reheated in oven about 10 minutes.

title: five-in-one bars
directions: Melt butter in cake pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle crumbs over butter and press them in the pan.
Sprinkle coconut, nuts and butterscotch pieces over the crust.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 3 to 4 dozen bars.

title: crunchy almond baked fish
directions: Mix crumbs, almonds and pepper.
Brush one side of fish with the melted oleo.
Dip buttered side into the crumb mixture and place on greased sheet pan, crumb side up.
Bake uncovered at 325° about 25 to 30 minutes or until it flakes easily.

title: cindie's garbage cookies
directions: Beat margarine, peanut butter, white and brown sugars until creamy.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add flours and baking soda; mix well.
Stir in nuts, wheat germ, oats, raisins and chocolate chips.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sandwich rolls
directions: Thaw bread in fridge for 6 to 8 hours.
Don't let rise. Stretch into rectangular pieces and put on a cookie sheet.
Spread a mixture of egg, parsley, oregano and pepper on dough.
Save part of egg mixture to spread on top of rolled dough.
Put on ham, salami, pepperoni and cheese.
Fold or roll bread over and seal edges tightly.
Spread egg mixture on top of dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Slice and eat.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Place whole chicken in large pot and cover with water to cover.
Cook until tender.
While chicken cooking, mix together cornbread, biscuits, sage, pepper and seasoned salt.
Set aside. Saute onion and celery in butter until transparent, but not brown, stirring often.
Add to cornbread mixture with enough broth to make a soft mixture (not dry).
Let this mixture set for 1 hour to improve flavor, then add eggs by stirring them in.
Do not beat. Place chicken in a greased roaster pan, breast side up.
Pour mixture over chicken and fill roaster full.
Bake at 350° until brown for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Arrange strawberries with points up in pie shells.
Cook remaining ingredients, stirring constantly until clear and bubbly. Pour evenly over berries.
Chill and serve with fresh whipped cream.
You can use other fresh berries and use complimentary flavor of dry jello.
Works very well with blueberries.

title: maple syrup corn bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended, but do not beat.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Cut into squares and serve warm with butter.

title: mg's baked rice
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Pat with oleo. Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.
Great served with chicken, shrimp or scallops.

title: haystacks
directions: Set oatmeal and cocoa aside.
In a large saucepan combine all other ingredients.
Cook until boiling.
Stir constantly for about 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Combine the oatmeal and cocoa. Stir and drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Chill until firm.
Store in airtight container.
Can substitute Rice Krispies or Cheerios instead of oatmeal.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder, alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, pineapple and juice and blend well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Place in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back.
Mix powdered sugar, butter and 1 cup drained pineapple and heat to boiling.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Toss first 2 ingredients.
Butter pan and add in order:
1/2 bread mix, next 3 ingredients and balance of bread mixture.
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over layers the beaten egg mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes until fluffy and nicely brown.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken breasts in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Placed Swiss cheese on top of raw chicken.
Mix stuffing according to directions on box.
Place it over cheese. Mix celery soup with 3 tablespoons milk and spoon over dressing. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove and let cool 15 minutes.

title: salad bar carrots
directions: Layer carrots, onion and pepper in a dish.
Mix the other ingredients and pour over the layered vegetables.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Pour the 4 cups boiling water over the wild rice and let stand 15 minutes in a bowl; drain.
Add soups, mushrooms, bouillon cubes, which have been dissolved in 1 cup boiling water.
Add bay leaf. Mix in seasonings.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add to first mixture.
Brown ground beef or pork sausage; drain fat.
Add to mixture and stir together.
Put in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with almonds (optional).
Bake covered for 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven or until rice is done.
Remove bay leaf.
This is the best!

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Separate cabbage leaves from head by removing core and cover cabbage with cold water.
Let stand about 10 minutes; remove leaves. Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water.
Cover and let stand until leaves are limp, about 10 minutes.
Remove leaves; drain.

title: lima beans
directions: Boil ham bone in large pot of water 15 to 20 minutes.
Rinse dry limas and add to water and ham bone.
(Can remove bone and pull ham from bone.)
Boil until water 1/2 gone.
Add water to fill 2 inches from top.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until done. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans for 1 hour in cold water, then cook, covered, for 1 hour.
In olive oil, saute onion, celery, garlic and green pepper.
Add to beans.
Cover bean mixture with water or chicken stock.
Add tomato sauce, oregano, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice or vinegar and ham hock.
Cook for 1 hour.
Remove skin from ham hock.
Cook another hour, then remove ham from bone and chop.
Return ham to soup.
Add chopped parsley to garnish each bowl.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Scoop out center; use bread pieces to dip.
Better made early; set in refrigerator.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle a few potato chips on top.
(These are not part of potato chips in ingredients; they are extra.)
Bake in an 8 1/4 x 8 1/4-inch Pyrex dish 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts in lightly salted water.
Remove chicken when done; retain broth.
Bone the chicken.
The spaghetti pasta can be cooked in broth.

title: pasta sauce(makes 12 cups)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil over medium heat in dutch oven for 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, stirring often, for 2 hours and 10 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: almond hershey pie
directions: Melt milk, marshmallows and Hershey bar together.
Cool in fridge.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly and put in baked pie crust.
Put in refrigerator.
When set, top with Cool Whip.
Wow!!

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together.
Makes 3 rolls.
Wrap each roll in foil with shiny side toward meat.
Seal tight.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Place in pan with rack.
Tilt rack, if possible.
Punch with fork 4 to 5 times in bottom end that is down.
Bake 90 minutes at 325°.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix flour, salt, egg white, oil, cream and water.
Beat until well moistened.
Coat onion rings with batter.
Fry a few at a time in deep fat until brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: hawaiian corn bread
directions: You need 1 square buttered pan.

title: chinese candy
directions: Melt chips; add noodles and nuts.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: great! cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, broth and seasoning in large boiler. Cook until tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine milk and flour until smooth.
Blend into hot vegetable mixture.
Add pepper to taste.
Cook until mixture starts to boil and thickens, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Cook about 5 minutes on medium heat.
May use other vegetables such as cabbage, cauliflower or a combination.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Plan 2 mushrooms per serving for a first course, six per serving for a main course.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix lemonade with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve with sugar wafer in small dish or make a graham cracker pie crust and make a pie.

title: olive-nut dip
directions: Combine and mix until well blended.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and flavoring.
Add flour, a little at a time, alternating with the eggs.
Begin and end with the flour. Add nuts, cherries and pineapple.
Bake in greased spring-form pan at 375° for 30 minutes.
Turn temperature down to 300° for 1 hour, then turn temperature to 275° for 15 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes, then turn out of pan carefully.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sugar.
Mix prepared Dream Whip with cream cheese and sugar.
Crush crackers and add melted butter (2 1/2 to 3 cups crackers).
Put part of the crackers in the bottom of greased 9 x 15-inch pan.
Add half of the cream cheese; spread with a fork if necessary.
Add 1 layer of cherry pie filling. Spread other half of cream cheese.
Sprinkle the rest of graham crackers on top.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo and 1 egg together.
Pat into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine cream cheese, 3 eggs and sugar. Pour over the first layer. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Cut into squares while warm.

title: peanut butter dessert sauce
directions: Cook, stirring constantly, margarine, flour and water until margarine is melted.
Add peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, beat until smooth with rotary beater.
Serve warm or cold over ice cream or cake.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken cutlets thin.
Lay slice of ham and cheese on top of each cutlet and roll up.
Hold closed with toothpicks or raw spaghetti. Roll in bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Pour melted butter over top.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: yummy gelatin punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sugar and stir until sugar dissolves, but don't boil.
Add cold water and let mixture cool, but not congeal.
Pour into a punch bowl and add the cranberry juice.
Add the ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 12.

title: sauerkraut and pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops shanks.
Mix everything else together in baking pan.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake in 325° oven for about 3 hours, covered.
(This may also be simmered on top of stove in covered pan.)
Serves 4.

title: strawberry crepes
directions: Slice strawberries; sprinkle with granulated sugar and set aside.
In blender, whip cottage cheese until smooth.
Stir in sour cream and confectioners' sugar.
Fill crepes with 2/3 of the creamy mixture and strawberries.
Top with remaining mixture and strawberries.
Serves 5-6.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large bowl, stir together sugar, flour, cocoa, powder, soda and salt.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla; beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water and pour into pan(s).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for round pans, 35 to 40 minutes for 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: one-cup cookies
directions: Cream together both sugars, margarine and oil.
Add egg and vanilla and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients (salt, soda, etc.) and mix in well.
Combine Rice Krispies, nuts, coconut and chocolate chips in separate bowl.
Add to cookie dough and mix well.

title: lemon buttermilk pie
directions: Combine and mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add buttermilk, yolks, melted butter and vanilla and blend.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, gently but thoroughly.
Pour into a raw pie shell.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool; serve with lemon flavored whipped cream.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together and cover tightly.
Mix 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.
Makes around 90 cups hot cocoa.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mix in double boiler the marshmallows and Pet milk or cream. When cool, pour over the remaining ingredients (in large bowl). Place in Pyrex dish and refrigerate until served.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix zucchini, onion, parsley, garlic, Bisquick, oil, salt and cheese; add eggs.
Put into 9 x 15-inch pan.
Drizzle oleo on top. Bake 35 minutes or more (until brown) at 350°.

title: sunkist lemon ice cream
directions: In large bowl, stir together cream and sugar until sugar is thoroughly dissolved.
Mix in lemon peel and juice.
Pour into 8-inch square pan or directly into sherbet dishes or scooped out lemon boats.
Freeze several hours until firm.
Garnish with lemon cartwheel twists, if desired.
Makes about 1 1/2 pints.

title: flavored coffee mixes
directions: For Mocha Coffee:
Two tablespoons of powdered cocoa.

title: country meatballs
directions: Shape beef, sausage, eggs, 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce and salt into 32 small balls.
Brown on all sides in 1 tablespoon oil.
Gently blend the cream of mushroom soup, water and 1 1/2 teaspoons Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve as main dish or appetizer.

title: fried veggies
directions: Cut up all your vegetables in bite size pieces.
Flour the squash and okra.
Put all the veggies in a skillet of hot oil and fry until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: homemade sauce
directions: In large Dutch oven, simmer onion in oil.
Pour in tomato sauce and tomato paste; stir thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer on low for 1 hour.
Add meatballs and/or cooked sausage; continue cooking for another hour.

title: funnel cake
directions: Heat oil in iron skillet until very hot.
Pour batter in stream, overlapping to connect the batter.
Fry until golden; turn over and cook the other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or cinnamon and powdered sugar mix.

title: grandma mcclellan's sand tarts
directions: Mix and chill overnight.
Decorate with nuts and egg whites.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Layer chicken; sprinkle with pepper and garlic.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over cheese and top with herb stuffing.
Sprinkle with butter.
Bake in a 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine and cook 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: seafood and pasta salad
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large pot.
Add pasta and cook, uncovered, 8 minutes or until tender but still firm.
Meanwhile, mix cucumber, mayonnaise, lemon juice, dill weed and garlic in a large bowl until blended.
Add seafood 30 seconds before draining pasta.
Add snow peas to pot.
Pour pasta and snow peas into colander; plunge colander into very cold water to chill contents. Drain well; add to dressing and stir to coat.
Spoon into serving plates.
Add 8 pieces tomato to each.
Makes 4 servings.

title: papa's pot pie
directions: Combine in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish the beans and stew, mixing well.
Arrange on top, the biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Mix all.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: stoney's meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Make loaf.
Bake roll for 1 hour at 350°. Add remaining "Meat Loaf Fixins" and bake another 10 minutes.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Mix butter, mustard, onion, Accent and poppy seeds.
Spread on inside of buns on both sides.
Add ham and cheese.
Wrap individually in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
(These work great for freezing and reheating for a quick snack!)

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix well and form into small balls.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil together all ingredients, except Velveeta, until smooth, approximately 5 to 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Turn off heat. Add 1 pound Velveeta cheese, cubed.
Stir well.
Serve.
Yum!

title: large christmas salad
directions: Use pineapple juice and water to make 3 cups of liquid for jello.
Cool.
Add grapes, pineapple and nuts.
Add cranberries that have been mixed with 2 cups sugar.
Add cranberries last to prevent forming too much juice.

title: golden bread puddin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bread crumbs in buttered 9-inch square baking pan.
In large bowl, beat eggs; stir in margarine or butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour evenly over bread, completely moisturizing bread.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool. Serve warm or chilled.
Serves 6 to 8.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: aunt florence's chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and baking soda. Add and mix slowly eggs and oil.
Continue blending and add boiling water with instant coffee.
Mix at high speed one minute. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: diabetic raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins, oleo, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Boil together for 3 minutes.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet by teaspoons.
