Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. These cookies do not spread when baking.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring the first five ingredients to boil.
Add raw peanuts. Cook to 300° or hard crack.
Remove from heat.
Add soda.
Stir and pour on buttered cookie sheet.

title: pink salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a pan.
Heat and stir until marshmallows melt.
Chill.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Chill.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; save grease and add onion and peppers to grease and saute until done.
Add pork and beans, mustard, brown sugar and catsup.
Mix all ingredients and put in casserole, adding crumbled bacon.
Place in oven and cook until juice thickens.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, egg, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add dry ingredients; blend well.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: rhubarb-strawberry pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust and place top crust over filling.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Make jello with water and melt marshmallows in it.
Then add cottage cheese, pineapple and pecans.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer until smooth.

title: california chicken
directions: Sprinkle soup mix
over
bottom
of
dish.
Spread rice over mix.
Lay chicken
on
rice,
then	pour liquid over all. Pour mushroom soup over all and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn bread mix.
Add the corn and mix together.
Brown ground chuck, then add it to the mix.
Add the cheese and pour into the bread pan.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix with mixer the cream cheese and milk.
Add cherry pie filling, then add the pineapple.
Mix. Add Cool Whip, marshmallows and mandarin oranges and nuts.
Fold into mixture well.
Best if chilled in refrigerator overnight.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Adjust oven rack to lowest position.
Heat oven to 400°.
Have ready a cookie sheet.

title: delicious sausage and egg souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease.
Add to beaten eggs.
Tear bread into pieces.
Add to egg mixture.
Add rest of ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate 12 hours. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: peanut butter and jelly cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir flour, sugar, and butter until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg and vanilla and blend well. Reserve 1/2 c. mixture for later.
Pour remaining mixture in baking pan and bake 10 minutes until lightly brown.
Remove from oven and spread jam over warm crust.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of peanut butter chips.
Mix together reserved crust mixture and remaining peanut butter chips and sprinkle over top.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut and clean out seeds of squash. Bake in pan with small amount of water at 350° until tender.
Remove from oven and cool. Peel off skin and mash squash in baking dish. Add butter, brown sugar and mix.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and bake until hot.
All winter squash is good this way.
Serves 6 to 8 people

title: vegetable polonaise
directions: Chop bread in blender.
Chop eggs and parsley.
In skillet melt butter and saute crumbs and egg.
Pour over vegetables. Serve hot.

title: thunderbolt kraut cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla together.
Sift flour and cocoa together twice and mix together real well.
Chop kraut real fine, measure and wash 3 times with cold water and drain.
Mix kraut in batter.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 30 minutes.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Combine Cheerios, all Chex and pretzels.
Coat with melted butter, Worcestershire sauce, onion and garlic salt and red pepper.
Bake for 2 hours at 200°; stir every 15 minutes.

title: microwave peppery cheese twists
directions: Line a 12-inch microwave-safe plate with waxed paper.
Mix flour, pepper and salt in a medium size bowl. Add remaining ingredients. Work in with a pastry blender or 2 knives until a soft dough forms.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out 1/4 of the dough at a time to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch long by 1/2-inch wide strips. Hold each strip by ends and gently twist. Arrange about 24 twists spoke-fashion around rim of prepared plate.
Place in oven on microwave-safe trivet or inverted saucer.

Microwave on High 3 1/2 to 4 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn once, until twists feel firm and are light golden. Immediately remove to wire racks to cool completely. Repeat with remaining dough. Store in tightly covered container up to 2 weeks. Makes 96.

title: sweet potatoes and berries
directions: Mix potatoes, cranberries and cinnamon together.
In separate bowl, mix butter, brown sugar, oats and flour.
Put on top of mixture in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 or more minutes.
Top with 1 cup marshmallows and brown.

title: london broil
directions: Trim excess fat off. Combine all ingredients. Use 1/2 on top of steak (brush on). Broil 4-inches from heat for 5 minutes. Turn and brush the other side with rest of the mixture.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes longer. Cooking time may vary for doneness.

title: salt substitute recipe
directions: Mix all seasonings together and put in your salt shaker.

title: tjack pannkaka (egg pancake)
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add flour and salt and stir in milk, a little at a time to make batter.
Put the butter in a 9x12 inch cake pan.
Place the pan over heat until the butter melts.
Pour the batter into the pan.

title: pumpkin impossible pie
directions: Put everything in blender and mix.
Pour in 10-inch pie pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana fritters
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix, sugar, milk, cinnamon, nutmeg and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.
Heat all ingredients on High for 8 to 9 minutes.
Dip 4 or 5 banana pieces into batter into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Remove with spoon.
Drain on rack.
Repeat frying remaining banana pieces.
May be sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Makes 24 fritters.

title: wassail
directions: Combine juices in large pot.
Tie spices in cheesecloth bag. Add to juice.
Heat and simmer until ready to serve.

title: perfection salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water, salt and lemon juice or vinegar.
Chill.
When mixture is slightly thickened, fold in cabbage, celery, carrots and onion.
Pour in mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce leaves and top with mayonnaise.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mary's wassail
directions: Combine cider, nectar, rum, brown sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon sticks in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 1 hour.
Stud oranges with cloves and add to cider mixture.
Serve hot.
Yields 1 1/2 gallons.

title: fennell and orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except lettuce.
Marinate at least 30 minutes.
Mix 2 times while marinating.
To serve, pour on a bed of lettuce leaves.
Wonderful as a summer salad served with grilled fish or chicken.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in water until barely tender.
Drain and chop coarsely.
Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Add flour, chicken broth and Worcestershire sauce and cook until thickened. Add milk and let come to a boil.
Add parsley and cheese.
Ready to serve when cheese has melted.
Add chopped cauliflower before adding cheese.

title: scalloped potatoes and franks
directions: Cook potatoes and onions with 1 teaspoon salt in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Slice frankfurters diagonally.
Mix with potatoes, onions, flour, salt, butter, 1/2 can of Hunt's sauce, cheese and parsley.
Spoon into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour remaining Hunt's sauce over.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.
Makes 2 servings.

title: jiffy pups
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Make a well and add milk.
Mix quickly.
Dip dry wieners in batter and deep fry until golden. Excellent reheated in microwave.

title: oatmeal sheath cake
directions: Spread on cake.
Put under broiler until brown.

title: amanda's apple cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
Fold in chopped apples. Add raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: tarragon chicken or pheasant
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil. Pour over chicken or pheasant that has been seasoned with salt and garlic. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Baste once or twice during baking.

title: fresh cranberry orange relish
directions: Grind cranberries and orange.
Mix with sugar.
Store in refrigerator until you use.

title: fruit cocktail cake i
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until blended.
Add:
1 medium size can of fruit cocktail and juice.
Stir until blended. Bake in ungreased 9x13 sheet pan at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes.

title: peanut butter wimsy
directions: Stir milk, sugar, melted butter and vanilla together.
Boil for 1 minute.
Turn fire off.
Add oatmeal and peanut butter. Stir until thick.
Put in pan and refrigerate.

title: oreo freeze
directions: In a
large
bowl
combine ice cream, crushed Oreos and Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: baked celery chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a shallow baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with salt (not very much) and pepper.
Mix celery soup (undiluted) and pimentos.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle herb salt on top. Bake 1 hour at 350° (moderate oven).

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add egg; mix well.
Spread onto bottom of pie shell. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture, being careful not to disturb it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in olive oil. Mix remaining ingredients and cook for 2 hours slowly.

title: chicken delight
directions: Coat pieces of chicken with flour. Salt and pepper.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine ketchup and cola. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: whipped cream pudding
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt and egg yolks together and bring to a boil.
Mix water with gelatine and stir in pudding mixture.
Beat egg whites and fold in pudding.
Beat cream and fold into mixture. Put graham crackers in bottom of pan.
Pour pudding mixture in pan and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Chill until well set.

title: hamburger bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole dish. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven kalua pork
directions: Rub rock salt and liquid smoke into pork surface. Wrap in leaves.
Enclose in heavy foil. Bake, covered, at 500° for 1/2 hour. Reduce to 325° and bake 3 1/2 hours.
Shred meat into bite size pieces and serve with roasting liquid. For different flavor, substitute banana, taro or spinach leaves for ti leaves.

title: bacon fritters
directions: Sift flour in bowl.
Add mustard, salt, paprika and pepper. Make a well in center and add the egg yolks and beat thorougly. Gradually work in dry ingredients.
Beat in enough beer to make a batter.
Cool for 2 hours.

title: grape hull pie
directions: Combine egg yolk, sugar, flour and grape hulls.
Cook to a boil.
Bake a 9 inch pie shell and fill with mixture.
Top with egg white meringue.
Bake until brown.

title: philly pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, softened cream cheese, oleo and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Add eggs; mix at low speed of electric mixer until blended.
Stir together flour and baking powder.
Gradually add flour mixture to cheese mixture, mixing at low speed until blended.
Pour into lightly greased and floured angel food pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool about 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Blend in beet liquid, vinegar and butter.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add beets to sauce.
Let stand 10 minutes or longer to blend flavor.
Serve warm.

title: microwaved apples with cinnamon
directions: Melt the butter in a microwave-safe bowl big enough to hold the apples.
Remove the seeds from the apples and slice each quarter into 4 thin slices and add to the melted butter.
Add the water, spices and sugar and toss until all the apples are coated well.
Cover dish with clear plastic wrap and microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir and re-cover.
Microwave for 2 more minutes.
Can be served over ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breast, save your broth to boil your spaghetti in. Saute your onions, peppers and butter. Mix all your soups together in a separate bowl. Cube your chicken breast and mix all ingredients (except grated cheese) together in a large casserole dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: basic potato salad
directions: Peel, cube and boil potatoes until tender (not mushy) and firm.
Boil 6 eggs (large).
Cool potatoes and eggs.
Chop eggs and pickles.
Add to the potatoes; mix in the mayonnaise, then sprinkle with sugar.
Stir.
Serve warm at room temperature or refrigerate and serve cold.

title: simple rolls
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Place a pat of butter or margarine in the cups of a 6-cup muffin pan.
Heat to melt butter. Divide dough into the muffin pans and bake at 350° until golden brown or about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Prepare noodles and spinach according to directions on package.
Chop tomatoes into 1/4 to 1/2-inch pieces.
In a greased 13 x 9-inch pan, layer 1/3 each noodles, Ricotta cheese, sauce, spinach, tomatoes and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle desired amount of spices over top of each layer.
Finish top of lasagna with Parmesan cheese and pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly on top.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
After baking, poke holes in cake.
Pour condensed milk over cake and let completely cool.
Mix coconut, marshmallow and Cool Whip.
Spread over cake and refrigerate.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to package instructions, using butter (not margarine).
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 3 1/2-inch pan. Allow cake to cool slightly in pan.

title: colonel's lady's salad bowl
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, in medium bowl, place frozen peas; cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.

title: orange meringue squares
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream the sugar, butter and egg until fluffy.
Add orange peel.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder with orange juice and milk.
Stir into first mixture.
Pour into baking pan.
Add topping before baking.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until crisp-tender, but not brown.
Blend in soup and milk.
Add tuna and pimiento.
Remove from heat.

title: corn, shrimp soup
directions: In a large pot (5-quart), saute seasoning in butter.
Add raw shrimp when seasoning is soft.
Cook until shrimp are pink, stirring often.
This is when I add about 1/4 teaspoon tarragon. Add Ro-Tel, V-8, corn and potatoes with water to fill pot, about 2 cups.
Cook on medium-low fire for about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are done.
Serve with garlic bread. Enjoy!

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat, taco mix and onion together.
Drain; add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
If desired, sprinkle more shredded cheese on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: custard pudding
directions: Melt butter with Grape-Nuts.
Beat eggs; blend in sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and the Grape-Nuts mixture.
Blend well. Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place in pan of hot water. Bake at 375°.

title: pork chops o'brien-beverly slimm
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Brown pork chops on both sides; drain.
Sprinkle chops with seasoned salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, vinegar and milk; cook until the mixture thickens and cool.
Combine the fruits, nuts and marshmallows with the egg mixture, then fold in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all together.
Pour in casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash until tender.
Drain and chop.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: mayfair cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add flour with cinnamon and salt.
Dissolve baking soda in 1 tablespoon milk and add to mixture.
Add chopped pecans.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow 325° oven until light brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook the chicken in the water seasoned with the bouillon.
Let cool.
Take chicken off bones; chop into cubes.
Mix chicken with the remaining ingredients.
Arrange on lettuce leaves; garnish with sliced apples that have been sliced, quartered and rubbed with lemon juice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: savory stew
directions: Put onion and carrot chunks in a large casserole.
Fry bacon and add to casserole.
Dredge meat in flour and quickly fry in bacon grease.
Add to casserole.
Saute garlic in same pan.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Have potatoes creamed.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Put 5 cups flour into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, salt, potatoes, potato water and melted shortening; stir well.
Add eggs, then yeast and water.
Add the remaining flour.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours, or until double in bulk.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until done.

title: molasses puffs
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by spoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: suzanne's m&m's cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Mix with Crisco and sugar.
Add 1 cup of M&M's.
(I use the browns and save the colorful ones for decorations.) Drop by teaspoonfuls to greased cookie sheet. Decorate the top with the remaining M&M's.
(Eat a few M&M's if you like.)
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Using
one
stick
butter,
saute
celery,
pepper
and onions.
In
a separate large bowl, mix peas, water chestnuts, pimento, mushrooms and soup.
Add sauteed vegetables and place in large
casserole
dish.
Top
with	bread crumbs which have been dipped in 1/2 stick of melted butter.
Bake at 450° until bubbly and crumbs are brown.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook rice.
Cook ground beef in a large skillet.
Add salt, rice and tomato sauce.
Cut the top off of the bell peppers and clean out the inside.
Stuff the ground beef mixture in the bell peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese on top after 25 minutes.

title: low-fat spinach lasagna
directions: First you need to make the tomato sauce.
Recipe is as follows:
Put one teaspoon of oil with chopped onions in a pot. When onions are golden brown, pour in 32 ounces of tomato sauce and 6 ounces of tomato paste.
Stir together for 10 to 15 minutes. Put one tablespoon of sugar and one teaspoon salt and one teaspoon of pepper.

title: german red cabbage(schmorekole)
directions: This recipe does not produce the same dish as served in restaurants but a darker, heartier version.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix together the butter, sugars, vanilla and water.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle morsels on top.
Place in preheated 375° oven for 1 minute and run knife through to marbleize.
Continue cooking for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: rice and broccoli casserole(quick-easy-delicious)
directions: Mix all ingredients and 1 cup of cheese together in a large bowl.
Season with salt, pepper and 2 teaspoons of garlic salt. Put in a large casserole dish.
Use remaining cheese for topping. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until cheese is melted and beginning to brown.
Serve with French bread.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli; put 1 cup mayonnaise, 1 chopped onion and 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Mix all together.
Add shredded cheese and bacon bits.
Mix all together.
Feeds about 6 people.
Very quick and easy to fix.
Do not cook broccoli.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 400° until set, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: creamed jumbo mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; slice stems.
Cut green onions into 1-inch pieces.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook mushrooms, stems, green onions, salt and pepper until mushrooms are tender, about 10 minutes, stirring often.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine hash browns, 1/2 cup margarine, chicken soup, American cheese, sour cream, salt and onion in casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes and remaining 1/2 cup margarine.
Bake at 350° (uncovered) for 45 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients in 2-quart pan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and is a thick mush.
Remove from fire and stir until cool.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat very hard after each addition.
Add baking powder.
Place in greased baking dish and bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with spoon.
Delicious served with dried beans.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish.

title: apple butter
directions: Add sugar and spices to apple sauce.
Cook until flavors are well blended.
About 15 minutes.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking as mixture thickens.
Pour into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch head space.
Process for 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: zucchini acapulco(microwave)
directions: Pierce skin and place whole zucchini in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook, covered with wax paper, for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes on High.
Rest for 5 minutes.
Soften cream cheese in dish on 30% for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Cut zucchini in half lengthwise and scoop out seeds and add to cream cheese mixture. Place this mixture back into the zucchini halves.
Sprinkle with paprika and microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on 60%, just until heated through.

title: daddy's potato salad doss' steak house(this is unusual and especially good)
directions: Boil potatoes until well done and drain.
Peel eggs and chop fine.
Mix all ingredients.
Mix mustard and mayonnaise together and then add to other ingredients.
(More mustard and mayonnaise can be added if needed for right consistency.)

title: plain cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly with a spoon.
Batter will be thick.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Set oven at 325° and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open door.
Will make its own delicious crust on top.

title: frozen mocha cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar
and
oleo.
Pat firmly on bottom and sides of
buttered	9-inch	spring-form pan or 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Chill.
In
large bowl beat cheese until fluffy. Add Eagle milk and
syrup, then add coffee and mix well.
Fold in whipped cream and
pour
into pan. Cover, freeze 6 hours or until firm. Garnish with more cookie crumbs.

title: texas treat
directions: Toss cereals, pretzels, peanuts and M&M's candies together. Melt white chocolate in microwave.
Toss with cereal mixture. Spread on waxed paper until cool.
Makes about 15 cups.

title: jello dessert
directions: Put the jello in the hot water and stir quickly.
Now put the cream cheese in; mush it around with a whisk.
When the cheese is melted in, whisk in the sour cream and let it set in the refrigerator until firm.
Top with a spoonful of whip cream when ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Add all other ingredients and mix together.
Put into casserole (covered).
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, or until it bubbles.

title: french dressing(much better than bottled)
directions: Just put in jar and shake until well mixed.
Refrigerate.

title: new orleans red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight.
Drain beans.
Put all ingredients except for rice in large stock pot.
Add cold water to cover ingredients.
Bring to boil, cover and lower flame.
Simmer over low heat for about 1 1/2 hours.
Prevent sticking by stirring and scraping sides every 1/2 hour.
If too thick, may add water. Cook rice as instructed and serve with beans.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In large kettle, cook onion in margarine until tender; stir in flour until smooth. Gradually add water, then broccoli, bouillon cubes and Worcestershire sauce. Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and broccoli is tender, about 10 minutes. Add cheese and cream. Cook and stir until cheese melts and soup is hot (do not boil). Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat butter and sugar; add vanilla.
Measure then add pecan meats.
Stir the pecan and cake flour into butter mixture.
Roll into small balls and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar when hot and again cold.

title: no fail pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and add eggs one at a time.
Add all other ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: southwest meatballs(serves 6)
directions: Combine ground meat, onions, eggs and bread crumbs in bowl, mixing well.
Roll into balls and brown in microwave oven or large skillet.
Drain well and add tomatoes and salsa; heat thoroughly. Serve over chips and top with cheese.

title: raisin clusters
directions: In saucepan, heat milk until hot (not to boiling).
Add chocolate chips; stir well until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add raisins; mix well.
Spoon clusters onto wax paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together and place in a covered jar.
I use at least 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: leola's strawberry upside down cake
directions: Place strawberries and 1/2 cup sugar in bottom of well greased pan.
Make a batter of 1 whole egg and 1 egg yolk, butter, sugar, flour, baking powder.
This batter is thick.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350° or until cake is firm.
Beat egg while stiff and put meringue on top and brown in 350° oven.

title: flo's lemon jello cake 2
directions: Beat all together well and bake in sheet pan (greased) 45 minutes at 325°, then glaze.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter; mix everything together and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: scramble
directions: Combine in a large flat pan all cereals, pretzels and nuts. In a small pot melt butter and add seasoning.
Seasoning amounts can be changed to suit personal tastes.
Bring mixture to a boil and drizzle over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat well and bake one hour at 225 degrees. Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in tightly covered containers.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Layer in pan, tortillas, chicken and soup mixture.
Add broth at the end.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350°.

title: cheese soup
directions: Put chicken broth and onion salt in saucepan and warm.
Add carrots and potatoes to broth and water.
After they have cooked awhile, mash with potato masher until in fine little bits.
Add milk and parsley, then add some soup mixture to the milk and flour sauce; stir until smooth.
Add this to rest of soup mixture.
Add cheese and stir constantly on low heat, being careful not to scorch.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in covered roaster. Start at 350°. Turn back to 275° after 3 hours. Continue at 275° for 3 more hours. Total time: 6 hours.

title: fruit cocktail pudding cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add egg and fruit cocktail. Nuts or coconut may be also be added if desired.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in long baking pan.
Cake is done if an inserted fork comes out clean.
It is particularly delicious if served warm with whipped cream.

title: potato chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash chicken.
Dip in butter.
Roll in potato flakes.
Pour 1/2 remaining butter in ovensafe dish.
Put chicken in dish, skin side down (if leaving skin on).
Bake 35 minutes.
Turn over and sprinkle a little of potato flakes over chicken.
Bake another 35 minutes or until a golden brown.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly the ingredients and store in sealed container. Use 1 heaping teaspoon for each cup of boiling water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put the 3 bars of cream cheese in a large bowl.
Chop chipped beef and spring onions.
Add to mix.
Add 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce and 1 tablespoon mix.
Mix together and form into ball.
Sprinkle paprika and chives onto ball.
Let set overnight for best flavor.
Serve with rye bread.

title: hershey's cocoa fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt; mix.
Stir in milk and place over medium-high heat until boiling, then reduce heat to medium-low and stir frequently.
Cook until forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat and pour into buttered pans or plates.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, egg, vanilla extract and almond extract, then stir in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Refrigerate dough; roll dough 3/6-inch.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes at 375°.

title: spanish delight
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Add tomato sauce, soup and chili powder.
Simmer.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix with meat and add corn.
Place in casserole dish; sprinkle with cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: linguini salad
directions: Toss with 1/2 bottle Salad Supreme seasoning.
Let stand overnight.

title: sugar twin fruit cake
directions: Boil the raisins in the water until dry.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add raisins last.
Pour into Pam sprayed tube pan or loaf pan.
(Mincemeat can be used instead of the raisins and apples.)
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.
This is good.

title: country cinnamon cake
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients and beat until smooth.
Mix last 3 (sugar, nuts and cinnamon) and layer with batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 9.

title: strawberry walnut bread
directions: Grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup walnuts in bottom of each pan; set aside.
In large bowl, stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, cardamon and nutmeg. In medium bowl, stir together eggs, sugar, strawberries, cooking oil, banana and orange peel.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Carefully stir in remaining nuts.
Put in pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove loaves from pan, cool completely. Wrap and store overnight before serving.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in casserole.
Place chicken on top of rice. Sprinkle with onion soup.
Mix mushroom soup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken. Bake, covered for 90 minutes in 350° oven.

title: marinated cabbage slaw
directions: Layer cabbage, onion and pepper in a salad bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bring oil, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and salt to a boil in saucepan.
Pour over layers.
Chill for 4 hours to overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fruit cake bites
directions: Mix fruit, coconut, peals and nuts together.
In separate bowl blend together condensed milk, butter, vanilla, and cracker crumbs. Add fruit mixture to batter.
Drop by spoon into lightly greased miniature muffin pans.
Batter should just reach top of cups.
Bake at 300 degrees 30 minutes or until lightly brown and solid feeling. Dust with powdered sugar while still hot.
Cool.
Remove very carefully from pan.
Yield about 3 dozen.
These are great for the holidays.
These store well.

title: oreo cookie torte
directions: Crush cookies and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan, saving some for top layer later.
Drizzle butter over crust.

title: grandma's frozen strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, jello and strawberries over low to medium heat. Heat to boiling; chill. Fold Cool Whip into strawberry mixture. Pour into pie crusts. Chill about 1 hour before serving.

title: macaroni hearty dinner salad
directions: Prepare dinner as directed.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In a large pot cook ground chuck and onion until meat is no longer pink. Drain well. Add Ro-tel and tomato juice and mix well. Add shredded cabbage and cook until cabbage is nearly done. Stir in red beans and season with salt and pepper to desired taste.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil; remove from heat.
Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add peanut butter mixture.
Sift flour and soda into the liquid mixture.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Arrange evenly in a greased 2-quart baking dish the potatoes, 1 tablespoon onion and parsley flakes.
Mix ground beef with milk, crumbs or oats, catsup, 1/4 cup onion and salt and pepper.
Spread evenly over potatoes.
Top with catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, 2 tablespoons milk and butter in medium micro bowl on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds. Stir until melted completely.
Spread in crust.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Arrange banana slices over chocolate.
Mix 2 3/4 cups milk and pudding.
Beat with wire whip 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon over bananas.
Spread with Cool Whip.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package.
Cook broccoli for a few minutes.
Combine the remaining ingredients except cheese.
Turn into buttered dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheddar-bacon eggs
directions: Remove bread crusts.
Cut bread into cubes.
Place in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, buttered.
Combine eggs and milk; mix well.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with bacon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine all ingredients together, cook until done.
Pour into pie crust, cool and serve.

title: five ices
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour into ice cube tray. Slice the banana on top and freeze until firm. Serves 4 to 6.

title: onion-cheese bread
directions: Put milk and onion in large bowl and let stand 10 minutes. Then add remaining ingredients and mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until browned and crusty.
Cut in squares.
Serve hot.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add tomato sauce, basil and salt; simmer 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Mix flour, eggs and milk together; dip chicken pieces in mixture to coat.
Saute chicken in olive oil until golden.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour tomato sauce over.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until chicken is done.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; mix with spaghetti sauce.
Spread small amount in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place a layer of uncooked noodles over sauces.
Cover with a layer of cottage cheese. Repeat layer 2 times.
Finish top layer with noodles, sauce and cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour in a 375° oven.
Remove from oven and let cool 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: wieners in sauce
directions: Lay wieners in long pan or baking dish with cover.
Spread hamburg over top of wieners.
Cut onion over top of hamburg. Season with salt and pepper. Pour tomato paste and tomato sauce into small bowl and add sugar.
Dilute if desired.
Mix well and spread evenly over wieners.
Cover and bake in oven at 250° for about 4 or 5 hours.
Serve in hot wiener rolls.

title: mary's blueberry pound cake
directions: Coat 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Press 1/4 cup sugar into oleo.
Cream 1 cup oleo and 2 cups sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla. Sift 2 1/2 cups flour, salt and baking powder.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Coat blueberries with 1/2 cup flour.
Fold into batter.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove.

title: german pancakes
directions: Mix eggs and milk. Add flour and salt to mix.
Leave lumpy. Melt butter in cast-iron skillet.
Place batter in skillet and bake at 350° until brown.
Season with powdered sugar and cinnamon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and put in buttered casserole and top with 1 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
This serves 5 to 6.

title: easy casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour (until the carrots are tender).

title: icebox cookies
directions: Beat eggs until light in small bowl at high speed.
Combine shortening and sugars in large bowl and cream well.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add nuts.
Add dry ingredients to shortening and sugars mixture.
Mix well for 4 or 5 minutes.
Form in rolls.
Place in refrigerator until hard or overnight.
Slice and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: christmas cupcakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, flour, soda, milk and cinnamon; mix well.
Add fruit and nuts.
Bake in smallest size paper cups in muffin tin at 250° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 200 to 300.

title: greek cookies
directions: Mix everything together until you can knead; form into oval shape.
Put on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 320° for 25 minutes.

title: egg rolls
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl, except peanut butter, oil, egg yolk, oil and wrappers.
Mix well.
Fry the mixture in 4 to 5 tablespoons of the peanut oil for about 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter and continue stirring until it melts.
Put in colander and drain.
Mix egg yolk with 1/3 cup water.
Brush egg yolk on outer edges of egg roll wrappers.
Spoon a heaping teaspoonful of filling on wrapper and roll.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except walnuts and parsley.
Refrigerate several hours.
Roll in ball and roll in walnuts and parsley. Serve with Wheat Thins.
Enjoy.
Great for parties.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread raw rolls out on large jelly roll pan.
Pinch seams together.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Beat together cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread over cooled crust. Spread on vegetables.
Press down slightly.
Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese.

title: hot tuna patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add flour and bread crumbs to tuna mixture.
Fry.

title: pommes dauphinoise(thinly sliced potatoes in creamy sauce)
directions: Layer potatoes in buttered ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle a little salt between layers.

title: dill pickles
directions: Boil vinegar, water and salt. Fill each hot jar with garlic, pepper, alum and dill seeds (one at a time). Pack with cucumbers and fill with vinegar mix. Wipe jar and put on hot lids and rings. This recipe works best using small cucumbers.

title: german chocolate snackin' bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate with margarine.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk, eggs, biscuit mix and vanilla.
Spread evenly into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a medium bowl, combine remaining milk and coconut; spoon in small amounts over chocolate mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on top; press
down firmly.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool thoroughly. Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature. Makes 36 bars.

title: tex-mex meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, beans, 1 cup of the picante sauce, onion, garlic, bread crumbs, eggs, cumin and salt to taste; mix well.
Press into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Carefully pour off drippings.

title: crab salad
directions: Place lettuce in bowl.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Mound mixture on top of lettuce.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: party dip
directions: With electric mixer or rotary beater, gradually blend soup into cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Mix remaining ingredients. Chill.
Serve as a dip with crackers or chips.
Makes about 2 1/3 cups of dip.

title: nectarine peach chutney
directions: This decorative platter is fast to assemble.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together.
Best when made the day before.
Serve with Doritos!!!

title: harvest hamburg casserole
directions: Saute all but cabbage
together
for
about 10 minutes; lay shredded cabbage in casserole.
Add sauteed ingredients on top; do not mix.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash, carrots and onion; drain and set aside.
Mix soup and sour cream; set aside.
Mix stuffing with margarine; line casserole dish with the mixture.
Alternate layers of vegetables and soup mixture, ending with soup.
Sprinkle more stuffing on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pretzel jello dessert
directions: Combine pretzels, oleo and sugar. Press into 9 x 13 pan for crust. Bake at 400 degrees for 8 minutes.

title: winter homemade vegetable soup
directions: Cook soup bone or meat and suet until almost done.
Heat beans, carrots, celery and onion in separate pot.
When hot, add to meat.
Cook until almost done and at last, add turnips, canned tomatoes and thyme.
Cook with low heat 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice and sweet condensed milk with electric mixer. Mix well. Pour into graham pie crust. Chill until firm.

title: foolproof rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar and lard.
When lard is melted, add cold water.
Add to this the eggs, salt and yeast cake, compressed and dissolved in lukewarm water.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Put dough in icebox until ready to use.

title: pineapple party punch
directions: Beat and blend the first 4 ingredients.
Add the ginger ale. Makes 24 punch cups.

title: dream kisses
directions: Mix.
Spread over first mixture after it has baked 10 minutes. Bake again 20 minutes at 375°.
Cut in squares as soon as taken from oven.

title: fudge squares
directions: Mix and melt in double boiler Crisco and bitter chocolate. Take off stove and add sugar, eggs, flour, salt and vanilla. Beat together well.
Grease 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan or a little larger and flour.
Spread mixture in pan.
It will just cover.
Press chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; set aside.

title: apple burritos
directions: Mix in pan and just heat.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.
You may top with raisins.

title: best baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic.
Add sugars, ketchup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses, chili powder and salt.
Stir in all of the beans.
Top with ham or bacon.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sara's lemon bars
directions: Cream together and press into a 2 x 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Beat eggs with water just to blend.
Set aside.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add green onions; stir-fry 30 seconds. Add eggs and scramble.
Stir in rice and cook until heated.
Add shrimp and soy sauce; cook until heated through.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine in mixer cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, dry mustard, garlic powder and Old Bay until well blended.
Add crab meat and mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 300 degrees for 55 minutes. Top with cheese.
Bake for five more minutes. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine shortening, brown
sugar
and
white sugar; add eggs, vanilla,
peanut
butter and sweet milk.
Mix in flour, soda, salt and oatmeal.
Bake at 350°.

title: spicy shrimp kabobs
directions: In blender, blend onion, garlic and ginger on high.
Add lemon juice and oil.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into bowl.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Add shrimp; toss.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Preheat the broiler or grill.
Thread the shrimp on 8 skewers.
Cook 4-inches from the heat source, 4 minutes per side or until cooked through.

title: kielbasa tortellini soup
directions: Saute garlic, onion and kielbasa in oil until kielbasa is browned.
Add broth, tomatoes, tomato paste, water, seasonings, carrots, celery and potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes. Add tortellini.
Return to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add broccoli and red pepper.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush crackers.
With crushed crackers, add melted oleo (1 1/2 bars or 3/4 cup).
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan as a crust.

title: apricot delight salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Combine other ingredients and blend.
Set aside to get firm.

title: fresh beef tongue
directions: Scrape tongue and wash well. Scald in boiling water. Place tongue and other ingredients in cooker.
Boil on medium heat for about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove skin from tongue while hot. Slice and serve.

title: tea party lemon bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Cream margarine, 3/4 cup sugar and lemon rind, then beat in eggs thoroughly, one at a time. Stir in flour mixture, alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir until smooth after each addition.
Turn into buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake in 350° oven, about 45 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center of bread comes out clean.
Stir 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice together and spread over top of hot bread.
Remove from pan after cooling, about 10 minutes.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Mix half of the flour and all other dry ingredients.
Heat liquids until very warm.
Add to dry mix; beat well.
Stir in rest of the flour to make stiff batter.
Spoon into two pans, greased and sprinkled with corn meal.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes, then bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.
Slice and toast.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add coconut, cornmeal and pineapple.
Mix.
Turn into unbaked pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Reduce to 325° and bake 35 minutes or until set.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar. Add eggs, margarine, buttermilk, vanilla and 2/3 cup coconut. Mix well.
Pour in pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter-chocolate bonbons
directions: Combine the powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine and peanut butter; pour over coconut mixture.
Blend until mixture is moistened. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
In another small saucepan, over low heat, melt the chocolate pieces with the shortening.
Spear the balls on wooden picks; dip individually into chocolate mixture to coat.
Place balls on waxed paper; chill to set.
Store, tightly covered, in a cool place.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Break up bread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown sausage and crumble over bread.
Beat eggs and add milk, mustard, salt and pepper and onion flakes.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle pan contents with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mock lobster
directions: Cut fillet of sole, scallops and shrimp into bite-size pieces and place in buttered 9 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over fish.
Cover with buttered flavored bread crumbs with added Parmesan cheese and extra parsley flakes.
Bake in 375° oven and bake for 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb and strawberry pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Mix with rhubarb.
Cut butter on top.
Sprinkle jello over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: doritos chip dip
directions: Layer ingredients beginning with cream cheese and ending with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven about 25 minutes or until heated through.
Serve hot with Doritos chips.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Mix well until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate until firm.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except peaches).
Add peaches and pour into raw pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mexicali dip
directions: Mash avocado, garlic, lemon juice and mayo.
Spread evenly in 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spread sour cream over.
Drain picante sauce and spoon over.
Top with layer of olives and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Yields 6 cups.

title: happy's pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour and salt.
Beat all ingredients well. Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for one hour.

title: honey date bran muffins
directions: Combine egg, honey, vegetable oil, water and cereal.
Let stand for 5 minutes, until cereal flakes are softened.
Add flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir to moisten.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 12 to 18 muffins.

title: coffee cake
directions: In a medium bowl, cream the butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Add the egg yolks.
In a separate bowl, sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately to the butter mixture with milk.
Add the egg whites.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Combine egg and sugar and mix well.
Add milk and vanilla. Stir well.
Gradually add milk to snow until blended.
Stir gently.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Trim peppers and boil shells for 5 minutes in salted water; drain.
Stuff with rest of ingredients; cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until peppers are tender and crumbs brown.

title: microwave apple butter
directions: In 3-quart microwave-safe dish, combine apples and cider. Microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey and onion in oil.
Add seasonings and tomatoes. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans and celery.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Serve with unsalted crackers or Italian bread.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender and mash.
Add salt, pepper, butter, onion, cheese and cracker crumbs.
Beat egg and add milk.
Add to squash mixture.
Bake in ungreased casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake choco-scotch clusters
directions: Melt over low heat the first 3 ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add rice Krispies and blend until well coated.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Let stand until cooled.
Makes 4 dozen (1 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Fry bacon for 5 minutes in a skillet and pour off about 1/2 of the fat.
Add onions and mushrooms and cook until onion is soft. Turn
contents
of skillet into the pastry shell and sprinkle with
cheese.
Pour
a
mixture of eggs, milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg
over
cheese.
Bake
at
350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Cut incisions in meat
and
fill with garlic.
Rub lamb with lemon juice, salt,	pepper, oregano and butter.
Place in roasting pan with water.
Bake
in
preheated
475°	oven
for about 1 hour or until browned.
Lower
heat to 350°; cover and bake until done. When meat	is
almost
cooked,
you
may add potatoes if you wish.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Saute onion in margarine until clear.
Beat egg lightly; mix with milk.
Cube bread and add to egg mixture, allowing bread to soak up moisture.
Add onions, turkey and seasonings.
Mix well. Microwave in plastic ring mold for approximately 9 minutes or when using a probe; bring to 170°.
Rotate 90° halfway through cooking. Let stand a few minutes before slicing.

title: diet punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: lemon chicken texas style
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rub chicken with garlic.
Grease baking dish large enough to hold chicken in one layer.
Put chicken in and sprinkle with lemon rind, oregano and thyme.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn pieces and continue baking for another 30 minutes.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Heat; do not boil.
Serve.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, without stirring. Remove from heat; add vanilla and then soda. Stir quickly and pour over corn quickly. Place corn in 2 or 3 large baking pans that have been well-greased. (Corn will at first look like it is not well coated, but this will even out during the baking process.) Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring well every 15 minutes. After corn cools, store in tight container.

title: beaufort stew(the pot)
directions: Fill large pot half full with water.
Add all seasonings to water plus sausage and potatoes.
Bring to rapid boil and boil 10 minutes.
Add corn on cob; bring to boil and boil 7 minutes.
Add shrimp and bring back to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Cut off heat and let set for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour water off and serve with butter, cocktail sauce, tartar sauce, slaw crackers or bread. Serves 10.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons of butter in a large skillet.
Add chopped mushrooms and cook 3 minutes.
Add salt and lemon juice; cover pan and continue cooking another 3 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove mushrooms from skillet and set aside.
Saute mushroom slices and set aside.
Melt remaining butter and stir in flour. Cook over low heat for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add chopped mushrooms and remaining ingredients, except parsley. Stirring continuously, cook until mixture is thickened and bubbly. Turn into top of chafing dish.
Garnish with parsley and sauteed mushroom slices.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: moist chicken
directions: Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise.
Place bread crumbs in large plastic food bag.
Add chicken, one piece at a time.
Shake and coat well.
Arrange on rack in broiler pan.
Bake in 425° oven for about 40 minutes or until golden brown and tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fig cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add melted butter and eggs and beat.
Slowly add remaining ingredients. Stir.
Pour batter into greased pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Add sauce when cake is done.

title: strawberry cream supreme
directions: Mix gelatine and cold water; add boiling water and sugar as well as the drained juice from strawberries.
Refrigerate until set but not jelled.
Add to gelatine mixture, angel cake broken into 1-inch pieces and whipped cream.
Fold carefully and then line a bowl with wax paper or Handi-Wrap.
Pour mixture into lined bowl and let set overnight.
Unmold and garnish with strained strawberries and any leftover whipped cream.

title: christmas crisscross cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, then roll into balls the size of a small marble.
Dip a fork in flour and press the cookies both ways.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
These can be sprinkled with red or green sugar or nuts, if desired.

title: brownies
directions: Mix above ingredients in order given.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let cool before cutting.

title: spiced raisin bars(diabetic diet adjustable)
directions: Combine molasses, eggs and shortening.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into mix; mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into a well-greased 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch or similar size pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown and leaves sides of pan.
Cool on wire rack, then cut into bar sizes.
Since this has only 1/2 cup sugar, you may adjust it into a diabetic diet.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Cook green peppers in fat until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add chicken to broth and milk.
Cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Add chicken; season with salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: mama's favorite sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Allow to boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
When sauce has cooled, pour over cool cake.
Sliced angel food cake tastes great.

title: macaroni hot dish
directions: Mix all together in casserole and refrigerate overnight or on countertop at room temperature at least 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Any cream or cheese soup would work well, also.

title: banana poppy seed cake
directions: Beat combined cake mix, water, oil and pudding mix until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Stir in poppy seed.
Pour into a well-greased and floured tube pan or Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake(sand cake when vanilla cookies used)
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and cream cheese.
In another bowl, mix together milk, pudding mix and Cool Whip. Combine the two mixtures.
In a large bowl, alternate layers of pudding mix with cookie crumbs, ending with crumbs.
Freeze or chill.
This can also be layered in a clean, foil-lined flower pot topped with silk flowers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown
meat.
Add
soup mix, mushroom soup and 1 can of water. Simmer
until
meat is tender.
Remove from fire.
Add flour and sour cream mixture to meat.
Serve over noodles.

title: fluffy cocoa frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour together until like a paste.
Cool, then add margarine or shortening, sugar and cocoa.
Also add vanilla.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Line two baking sheets with foil.
Lightly grease foil.
Knead almond paste to soften.
In a food processor, or with an electric mixer, mix almond paste, cocoa, granulated sugar and egg whites. Beat on low until well blended.
Add powdered sugar and flour. Continue to beat until thoroughly mixed.

title: ooie gooey butter cake
directions: Melt butter, add box of yellow cake mix.
Add 2 eggs and mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan evenly.

title: tourtiere(french canadian pork pie)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; cut in Crisco or lard.
Mix beaten egg with vinegar and add cold water to make 3/4 cup of liquid.
Sprinkle egg mixture on flour mixture and toss with a fork.
Use at once or store in fridge for several weeks. This may also be frozen.

title: 8-minute cheesecake(diet)
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually add in Equal.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries, if desired.

title: sesame chicken breast
directions: Blend
together eggs, water, soy sauce, salt and pepper in
a shallow
dish.
Dip
chicken
into flour, then into egg mixture and
then sprinkle both sides with sesame seed.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add chicken, turning to coat with butter. Bake
in
a hot oven (400°) for 40 to 50 minutes until golden brown and tender.

title: fruit spears
directions: Note: You will need toothpicks and a plate.

title: pickled pears
directions: Mix all together in a pot, then pour into jars.
When they start to turn pink, they are ready.

title: caty's cracker balls
directions: Mix the marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Crush the crackers and put into a bowl.
Take a small amount of marshmallow cream mixture and form into a ball.
Roll in the cracker crumbs.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Put small amount of oil in pot. Add cubed pork chops and fry. Put tomatoes in blender with
peppers and juice from garlic and chop. Add chicken cubes to pork chops. Add chopped onion with pork chops. Next add mixture from blender to pork chops. Add water to desired thickness. Add
corn and tomato sauce. Let stew cook for approximately 45 minutes and serve in tortillas.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Mix and freeze in containers.
Take out of freezer about 15 to 30 minutes before serving, so it becomes slushy.

title: flowerpot cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Fold nuts into batter.
Place ice cream cones in muffin cups or jelly roll pan; fill with batter to within 1-inch of tops of cones.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti as instructed on package.
Put oil in pot (1 teaspoon) to keep it from sticking together.
Cool.
Add all ingredients, then add 1/2 bottle salad dressing and other ingredients, seasoning to taste.
Chill.
This will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.
May add more salad dressing before serving, if not moist enough.

title: deer loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Add 1/2 cup barbecue sauce and mix again.
Form into an oblong loaf.
Spread 1/2 cup barbecue sauce on top.
More may be used, if desired. Then drizzle half the honey over all.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.
Remove loaf and repeat barbecue sauce and honey method over all when loaf is half done.
You may brown the top for additional flavor.
So good.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift
together the first 4 ingredients.
Cream the oil, sugar and
eggs.	Mix
wet
and
dry
ingredients
until well blended. Add the vanilla, carrots, nuts and raisins.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour
mixture
into a greased and floured pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cucumber slices
directions: Combine 2 parts canned deviled ham with 1 part cream cheese. Spread on washed and scarred cucumber slices (1/4-inch thick).

title: chili grande
directions: Brown beef in large skillet; transfer to large kettle.
Saute onions and garlic in remaining skillet drippings.
Add all spices and liquids.
Mix well and simmer for 2 hours.
Thicken with flour or cornstarch or thin with beer to preferred consistency. Spices and peppers may be varied to suit personal preference.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: First I put the chocolate chips in.
Then I put the oranges in!
And then I put the butter in and then I put the eggs in. Then, stir it!
And then I stir it fast!! Then I put butter in and then we put it in the stove.
I don't eat them.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter on low heat. Mix sugar, flour and salt together in mixing bowl. Beat eggs. Add flour mixture to eggs. Combine with chocolate mixture. Mix well. Add vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie crust, thin kind. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 300° to 325° oven. Cool on rack.

title: icing
directions: Boil milk and flour until thick, cool.
Mix shortening and butter.
Add cooled paste.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Spread on cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut or tear chicken into bite size pieces, put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup, onion soup mix and sour cream together.
Spread on top of chicken.
Make stuffing according to directions, using reserved chicken broth instead of water. Spread stuffing over top and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover last 15 minutes.
Yields 8 large servings.
Can be prepared ahead of time, refrigerated and then baked.

title: pat's eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant, chop and cook in salted water, along with onion, until tender.
Drain well.
Add crackers, cheese, beaten egg, margarine and milk to eggplant.
Put in buttered baking dish and bake on 350 until bubbly and slightly browned, about 45 minutes.

title: lemon oatmeal crisps
directions: Beat together butter and sugar until creamy.
Add egg, vanilla and lemon extract; beat well.
Sift together flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Beat in oats.
Using 1 teaspoon measure, drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for 7 to 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheets while hot.
Cool thoroughly before stacking.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: microwave broccoli and cheese
directions: Wash and cut broccoli.
Steam or boil it.
In microwave, melt butter in a glass dish.
After melted, add flour and stir quickly. It will be thick.
Warm milk in microwave and add to butter and flour.
Cook in microwave 8 minutes on High, stirring occasionally. Stir in cheese until melted.
Serve over drained broccoli.

title: *eggplant dip
directions: Pierce the eggplant and bake whole or broil, turning constantly, until tender.
Cut in half and spoon out pulp.
(Use a Foley mill to strain seeds.) To pulp in bowl, beat in olive oil and lemon. Add all the other ingredients.
Chill overnight. Garnish with black olives and tomato wedges.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl beat egg yolks.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, lime juice, rind and food coloring.
In small bowl stiffly beat 1 egg white.
Fold into sweetened condensed milk mixture.
Turn into shell.
Beat reserved meringue with cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Put meringue on pie.
Chill before serving.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mix and let boil 1 minute.

title: oyster stew
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the undrained oysters and salt. Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes or until edges of oysters curl.
Stir in milk and cream.
Heat through.
Season to taste with additional salt and pepper.
Sprinkle each serving with paprika and top with a pat of butter or margarine.
Makes 4 servings.

title: linguini primavera
directions: In a nonstick skillet (or one sprayed with butter flavored Pam) over medium heat, cook broccoli, carrots, onion, Italian seasoning, garlic and pepper in chicken broth for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato; cook another minute or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Toss with hot linguini, Egg Beaters and Parmesan cheese.
Servings:
6 main dishes.
Fat:
1.5 gms. Calories:

title: fruit punch
directions: Add the above ingredients and fill with water to make one gallon.
Add two quarts of ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: clam casserole
directions: Use juice from 1 can clams.
Put in 18 x 25 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Warm milk; add sugar.
Stir until the sugar dissolves.
Blend milk mixture with eggs and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Bake at 375° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake
in
a
x 13-inch pan a yellow cake according to directions
on the box.
After the cake is done, punch holes in it with
a wooden spoon.
Mix milk, coconut and cream of coconut; pour
over
the cake.
Pour 1 small can crushed pineapple with juice.
Mix
large
container of Cool Whip with frozen coconut. Spread
over cake.
Wrap in foil and store in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: brisket in beer
directions: Put sliced onion over brisket.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over brisket.
Cover; bake at 350° until tender.

title: marble chocolate mousse pie
directions: Heat both chocolates, milk and vanilla.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Take whipping cream, beat until stiff.
Add cream to mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill.

title: taco pizza dip
directions: Mix avocado dip with sour cream.
Layer ingredients as listed on a 12-inch round platter or large cooking sheet.
Serve with chips.

title: caramel corn
directions: Set oven at 225°.
Put large pan in heated oven.
Pop corn (air-popped is best) and put in pan in oven to keep warm.
In separate large pan, mix sugar, corn syrup, margarine and salt. Heat, stirring constantly until melted and bring to a boil, making sure all sugar is blended.
When it reaches soft ball stage, remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
(The mixture will froth.)
Pour over popcorn and mix thoroughly until coated (use fork).
Put back in oven, set timer and, every 15 minutes, turn coated corn, mixing well.
In 60 minutes, remove from oven and cool.
Store in covered bowl.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder and set aside. Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Alternately add flour mixture with one cup of milk.
Add vanilla and beat mixture until light and fluffy.
Add walnuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Bring soup and milk to a boil.
Add salt and garlic salt. Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and soup in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with 1 cup of butter.
Cover. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and bake for 15 minutes.

title: pizza nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Arrange tortilla chips in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Top each chip with some of the spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle evenly with oregano and cheese.
Bake until cheese is just melted, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: christmas muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Nabisco bran and let cool.
Add sugar, Crisco, buttermilk, flour, soda and salt.
Mix well and add Bran Flakes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes in greased muffin tins. Raisins or dates can be added to batter before baking.
Batter can be kept in refrigerator for 1 month.

title: spice cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: parsley dumplings
directions: Mix flour and butter as with pie crust. Stir and mix well all ingredients with milk.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add pretzels.
Press in a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 325° for 6 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, Creamettes, pimentos and cheese in large bowl. Heat together the 2 cans of soup, milk, chicken broth and margarine.
Pour over the chicken.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbles and browned, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Put cranberries and oranges through food grinder using medium blade. Stir in remaining ingredients. Chill several hours before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: hoppin' john(creole black-eyed peas)
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, keeping drippings in pan.
Saute onion, peppers and celery in drippings until tender.

title: fish souffle
directions: Preheat oven to moderate (350°).
Grease 2-quart casserole.

title: veal piccata(italian)
directions: Gently pound the veal until thin and flat, but not broken. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dredge lightly in flour.
Heat olive oil in pan.
Add veal; turn up heat and saute veal quickly. Drain off grease and add beef stock, lemon juice, butter and parsley.
Stir well; heat sauce thoroughly.
Spoon sauce over veal scallops to serve.
Serves 6.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: quick mediterranean fish
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwave dish, add onion, oil and garlic. Cover and cook on High 3 minutes.
Drain. Add tomatoes, salsa and cinnamon over top of fish.
Cover and cook on High 3 to 4 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.

title: bootleg beans
directions: Fry bacon until half done, then add onion.
Brown.
Pour off most of grease.
Add pork and beans, brown sugar, vinegar and ketchup.
Simmer, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: apple betty
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle with orange juice.

title: caramel pecan cake
directions: Melt candy bars and oleo in saucepan.
Cream cake mix, water and eggs.
Add to candy bar mixture and stir together.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: christmas nuggets
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cream thoroughly shortening, butter and confectioners sugar.
Blend in vanilla and nuts. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix until dough is smooth and well blended.
Shape into small balls, place on ungreased cookie sheet, flatten slightly.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: polly's casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions; add meat and cook.
Add tomato soup, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cream cheese at end so chunks of cheese don't totally melt.
Meanwhile brown mushrooms in butter.
Grease casserole dish.
Cook and drain noodles.
Pour meat mixture into greased casserole dish.
Spread mushrooms and corn flakes on top. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes; 5 minutes before finished baking, add chopped almonds on top.

title: zinger
directions: Combine juice and soda.
Add crushed ice.
Serve in a glass with rim dipped in salt.
Makes 1 serving.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook a few minutes and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: colcannon
directions: Cook and mash potatoes; fold in shredded cabbage and scallions that have been cooked with milk.
This recipe can be cut in half or doubled, depending on amount to feed.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water in a 9 x 9-inch dish.
Cool.
Add carrots and pineapple.
Refrigerate.
Serve when firm.

title: cranberry pudding
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg, milk and sifted dry ingredients.
Last, add vanilla and cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal vegetable quiche
directions: Combine cheese, eggs, dill and salt.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into greased 10-inch quiche pan.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese. Bake until quiche is set in the center for 35 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with sliced tomatoes.

title: potato-egg-sausage casserole
directions: Fry hash browns and onion, press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Fry sausage and sprinkle over hash browns.
Mix eggs and soup together and pour over top of mixture.
Mix well in pan.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: evelyn's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.	Good.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
When done, poke holes in cake using a fork.
While cake is baking, dissolve jello in hot water.
Add frozen strawberries to jello and stir until strawberries are thawed.
Pour this over the cake while cake is still hot.
Let cool and then spread Cool Whip on top.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
As soon as biscuits come out of oven, brush with mixture of butter and garlic salt.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into batter.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: garbanzo beans with tahini
directions: Mix garbanzo beans, salt, garlic, lemon juice and tahini in the blender until they get smooth.
Then place the beans in a plate; top with oil and parsley.

title: chicken vermicelli
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Cook chicken and vegetables, stirring constantly 5 minutes or until done. Add cup of soup blended with water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 5 minutes or until thick.

title: fluffy banana cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Put in large bowl the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes.
Stop and add buttermilk.
Add sifted flour mixture alternately with mashed banana.
Beat only enough to blend, about 2 minutes.
Pour batter into 9-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 35 minutes.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: grandma evans' pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar, pumpkin, salt, ground cloves, ginger and cinnamon. Mix well. Stir in milk. Turn into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° for about 40 minutes or until set.

title: white christmas pie
directions: Blend 1/2 cup sugar, flour and gelatine.
Stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, over
medium heat, just to boiling.
Chill in refrigerator; stir occasionally until mixture mounds when dropped by spoon.
Stir in flavorings.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until frothy.
Slowly add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff and glossy.
Don't overbeat!
Fold in whipped cream and coconut.
Pile into prepared pie shell.
Chill 4 hours or longer.
Very good served with crushed strawberries or raspberries.

title: more
directions: Saute ground beef and onion.
Add tomato paste and water and simmer.
Add chili powder.
Corn may be added to mixture.
Cook noodles and drain.
Arrange in casserole dish the noodles, meat sauce and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend flour and salt; add water and oil.
Stir with fork. Form into ball.
Roll out between 2 sheets of wax paper, 12-inches square.
When dough is rolled out to edges of paper it will be the right size for crust.
Peel top paper away.
Fit dough into pan, wax paper side up.
Remove wax paper.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: black forest dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; spread over cool crust.
Mix puddings as directed on box; 2 to 3 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 35 minutes or until set at 350°.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine everything but coconut in blender for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes, then top with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pretty pineapple
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple.
Leave the pineapple in the can, but make sure all the juices are out.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Pour it into the can.
Chill at least 3 hours.
To unmold, dip can into hot water.
I run hot water over the bottom of the can a few times until I feel it loosen.
Cut out the bottom, but please put a saucer or your hand over the top while opening the bottom, then slide or push out the molded fruit.
Turn it on its side and slice.
You'll have as many servings as you have slices of pineapple.

title: pork chop or chicken breast casserole
directions: Pour rice packet and seasoning packet into flat Corning Ware casserole dish.
Add 2 cups of water and stir mixture together. Salt pork chops or chicken breasts liberally.
Slice mushrooms if they are available.
Place them in the water with rice mixture. Lay pork chops on top of other ingredients, cover and bake at 350° to 375° until water is absorbed (approximately 1 hour).
Serves 4.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar together.
Start with four drops of flavoring and then carefully add flavoring and color as desired.
Knead until pie dough consistency is achieved.
Add sugar to make softer or decrease sugar for a firmer consistency. Take small pinch and roll into a ball in granulated sugar.
Press into mold.
Remove excess and unmold at once onto waxed paper.

title: applesauce cake *
directions: Cream shortening (the butter) and syrup; beat in eggs, then 1/2 of the applesauce and soda and water.
