Add 1/2 dry ingredients which have been sifted together, then rest of applesauce and pineapple mix and add rest of dry ingredients.
Add coconut, nuts and raisins that have been floured.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Mix stuffing and onions and celery.
Put in greased long baking dish.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake until brown in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: turkey pasta salad
directions: Combine turkey, macaroni, celery and onions.
Mix well. Combine mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Mix all together.
Chill before serving.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix ingredients together well and roll into about 40 balls. Roll in more powdered sugar.

title: quick wheat bread
directions: Stir first three ingredients together in a small bowl.
Let stand in warm place.
In a large bowl, beat together egg, 1 cup water, sugar, margarine and salt.
Stir in yeast mixture.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time; mix well.
Mix in last cup of flour by hand.
Divide the dough and place in two greased loaf pans.
Cover with damp cloth or Saran and let stand until doubled in bulk (about an hour).
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In saucepan, melt Butter and Sugar.
Add Cocoa, Milk, and Oatmeal; mix together.
Spoon onto cookie sheet to cool.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water; pour in peanuts.
Boil over medium heat until liquid is gone, stirring frequently.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: tart shells
directions: Have margarine and cream cheese at room temperature. Add flour and roll into small balls.
Put in small tart size muffin pans. Shape to pan.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen. These freeze well.

title: banana-strawberry smoothies
directions: Peel bananas, cut into chunks.
Place ingredients into blender, blend on high speed for about one minute or until mixture is smooth.
Makes 2 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Place 1/2 of cookie crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat sugar, cream cheese, vanilla and milk until smooth.
Then add pudding mix.
Beat until creamy.
Pour over crumbs, then add other 1/2 of cookie crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cold artichoke soup(serves 6)
directions: Combine and puree in food processor.
Chill well.

title: chicken for a king
directions: Melt the tablespoon of butter and grease the bottom of a casserole dish.
Next, stir in onion, green pepper and celery. Pour mushroom soup and one can of water over rice and ingredients. Add large can of mushrooms.
Lay the four chicken legs on top. Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in oven at 350° and bake one hour.
Makes four servings.

title: boeuf bourguignon
directions: Dredge beef in flour and seasonings; brown in oil and transfer to Dutch oven.
Saute onion, carrot and garlic until tender; add to Dutch oven.
Add Burgundy, broth, tomato paste, parsley, thyme and bacon; cover and simmer until tender (about 1 1/2 hours). Saute mushrooms and add before serving.
If sauce is too thin, thicken with Burgundy and cornstarch.
Serve over noodles, mashed potatoes or baked potatoes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour over bread pieces that are layered in baking dish.
Add butter.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: cookie kisses
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and flour; mix well and chill.
Form into balls; press around Kisses.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 12 minutes at 375°.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: old fashioned corn pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, combine milk, corn and cornstarch. Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt. Pour into a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Spoon melted butter over top. Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until top is brown and pudding is set, not soupy.

title: best hot chocolate
directions: Place the ground chocolate into each mug.
Stir in very hot milk.
Top with whip cream, if desired.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: In a bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta cheese, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Spoon 1/3 of mixture into baking dish.
Cover with 1/3 of tomato slices and 1/3 of the Mozzarella cheese; repeat layers. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In skillet, cook ground beef and onions until brown and drain.
Add taco mix and water; simmer 20 minutes.

title: denise emery's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla together.
In a large bowl, mix flour, salt and soda together.
Then add oats and nuts. Stir sugars, shortening and eggs into dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and drop onto cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Be sure to leave space between them for spreading.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until slightly brown.
Remove before very brown for a softer cookie.
Will be soft at first, but will firm up.
Cool and ice with glaze, if you choose.
A very thin glaze is best.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Cook for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Stir until oats are coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: quick vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: purple ape
directions: Pour grape juice into blender. Add ice cream. Cover and whirl just until blended. Pour into glasses and serve immediately. Yields 4 servings.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs. Place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each cupcake paper. Pour batter over wafer. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool, then top with pie filling. Makes 24.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients; chill.
Serve with vegetable dippers or crackers.

title: 5 layer squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and boil until tender.
Drain well.
Melt butter, add chopped onion and cook in butter until tender.
Crumble crackers in bowl.
Pour butter and onions into the crackers and mix until well coated.
In a 8 x 8 baking dish place:

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 23 to 28 minutes or until done.

title: italian chicken
directions: *I like to use Barilla brand (marinara sauce). But if you don't have Barilla, any jar sauce will do.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Layer bread and cheese.
Combine rest of ingredients in blender; pour over layers.
Add more milk if mixture isn't moist. Cool overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° with dish set in water.

title: pumpkin meringue pie
directions: Blend dry ingredients in top of double boiler.
Add milk, then yolks and pumpkin, stirring until creamy.
Cook 20 minutes.
Pour into shell.
Top with meringue.

title: baked cheese omelet
directions: Skin and slice tomatoes, cook in a little margarine in a saucepan, and then pour into a greased pie dish.
In the same pan, with a little more margarine, add the milk and the slightly beaten eggs.
Cook over low heat, stirring as for scrambled eggs, until just beginning to set.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion about 1/4-inch thick.
Layer squash, onion, salt, pepper, half of Cheddar cheese, 4 slices bacon, crumbled, half of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
In small saucepan, melt margarine and add bread crumbs.
Add to casserole, bacon drippings and milk, then top with bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: carol's dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender.
Serve with celery, carrots or mixed snack crackers.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix first amount of sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt. Gradually add hot water, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick. Add egg yolks, butter, lemon juice and rind.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry.

title: strawberry yum yum
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, butter and nuts until crumbly and press into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and break so mixture is crumbly.
Set aside.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and sugar; then add egg, milk and oil.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Bake in 8-inch square baking pan at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat together all ingredients, except Doritos, until Velveeta cheese is melted.
Stir constantly as it will stick.
Add Doritos to mixture.
Pour in two 8-inch square serving pans or whatever size you want.
Mixture is runny but will become firmer when allowed to sit for a while.

title: carrot apple cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; blend thoroughly. Sift together dry ingredients and add to the first mixture and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients except frosting.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until center of cake is firm to touch.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and finish cooling on cake racks. Frost with vanilla frosting.

title: classic banana cream pie(preparation time: 15 minutes)
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine or butter and vanilla. Cool slightly.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Mix flour with salt and pepper to taste.
Dredge meat in flour and brown in oil with onion.
Add tomato juice, water and sugar. Simmer until tender.
Ten minutes before serving, add mushrooms and sour cream.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water, butter, salt and pepper for 15 to 20 minutes.
Save broth.
Mix stuffing according to package directions.
Mix all cans of soup together, adding chicken broth. Put 1 layer of stuffing in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Break chicken breasts into bite size pieces and put a layer on stuffing. Pour a layer of soup on top.
Continue until all is used up. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: american apple pie
directions: Mix apples, sugar, flour and spices in large bowl.
Let stand 2 or 3 minutes.
Then mix a little more; pour into a 9-inch pie shell and add another pie shell on top.
Press shell down slightly and cut tiny slits in crust.
Brush top with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk. Beat until thick. Add cool whip and Eagle Brand milk. Mix well. Layer with wafers and bananas. Makes about 3 layers in large bowl. Refrigerate.

title: hawaiian pies
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar and flour.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup of boiling water and add to pineapple mixture.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into baked pie shells.
Refrigerate to set (about 1 hour).
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: seafood casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter and mushrooms and saute for 5 minutes.
Stir flour and combine well.
Add the cream, a little at a time, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Add the sherry; cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in mayonnaise, parsley, scallions and bread crumbs, then fold in the crabmeat and lobster.

title: pumpkin ice cream squares
directions: Let ice cream soften so it will mix easier.
Mix and press crumbs, sugar and butter into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Combine pumpkin, brown sugar and spices, then fold in ice cream and pour into pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Cut into squares about 20 minutes before serving.
Top with whipped cream (Cool Whip) and nuts.
Rich, but good.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in small bowl.
Toss remaining ingredients in a serving bowl.
Stir in dressing; serve chilled.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: peach parfait pie
directions: Let peaches stand 15 minutes; drain syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup and boil.
Add gelatin and cold water.
Cut ice cream into 6 pieces and add to liquid.
Stir until melted.
Chill about 20 to 30 minutes.
Fold in peaches.
Pour into cooled pie shell. Chill several hours.
Top with cream and peaches.

title: lollipops
directions: Lightly butter baking sheet, arrange sticks on sheet.
Combine butter, corn syrup and sugar in heavy 1-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stir occasionally.
Reduce heat, continue cooking until a drop in cold water separates into threads - hard but not brittle.
Stir in food color.
Pour over end of sticks.

title: acini de pepe salad
directions: Boil acini de pepe in salted water until water is gone.
Drain fruits, saving juices.
Cook juices with eggs, flour and sugar until thick.
Add acini de pepe and let stand overnight.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery in cooking oil in 6-quart pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Uncovered, bring to boil, then cover and simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine and bake for 35 minutes at 350 degrees all of the above ingredients.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cut in half and scoop out centers. Mash centers.
Add salt, butter and milk; mix.
Add diced tomatoes and chopped green onions.
Now fill potato skins and eat.

title: easy pierogi(polish style)
directions: Force cheese through sieve until free from lumps or run through food processor until smooth.
Add butter, egg yolks, salt, sugar and flour.
Add well beaten egg whites and fold in carefully.
Turn out on floured board.
Roll with hands; space into long, narrow rope.
Flatten and cut slantwise into pieces 2 inches long.
Cook in salted water until they rise to the top. Lift with a straining spoon and cover with lightly buttered crumbs.
They are delicious with sour cream flavored with cinnamon and sugar.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and dry strawberry gelatin.
Add oil and milk; mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add frozen strawberries and mix.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Oven toast pecans in butter and salt.
Mix cream cheese, milk, beef, green pepper, onion and pepper.
Fold in sour cream and half of nuts.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle remaining nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish with Melba rounds.

title: iceberg cucumber pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and soak in lime water for 24 hours.
Wash several times.
Soak for 3 hours in clear water, changing water every hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Measure milk in blender.
Add rice and eggs.
Blend to chop rice.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Stir milk mixture into cornstarch mixture in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Chill.

title: cheese and sausage biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand. Roll into small balls or drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 315° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cauliflower salad(make 24 hours ahead)
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon in 11 x 16-inch pan.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan cheese and spread over the top.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss lightly before serving. Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain. Stir in sauce mix, garlic and tomato sauce. Heat until bubbling.

title: ginger bread cutouts
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, egg and extract.
Add dry ingredients. Flour board; roll out and cut in desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: curried baked fruit(prepare the day before)
directions: Drain all fruit.
Add sugar and cinnamon to melted margarine. Arrange fruits and nuts in layers in casserole dish (long glass baking dish).
Pour margarine mixture over all the fruit mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Refrigerate overnight.
Reheat at 350° before serving.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat in fondue pot and serve warm as a dip for crackers.

title: cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut
Xs
in
top of bread almost all the way through to bottom,
but leave 1 inch uncut on each end. Wrap in foil halfway up
to
support bread (do not cover top). Fold cheese and stuff
into the X-cuts which form cups. Combine seasoning mix
(butter,
onion,
mustard,
Beau Monde, lemon juice and poppy seed) and
spread
on the top.
Place on cookie
sheet on bottom rack
of
oven.
Bake
at
until cheese
melts, about 10
to
minutes.
Serve
informally, letting guest pull off chunks of bread from the loaf.

title: "ole time" potato casserole
directions: Using a 2-quart casserole dish, layer potatoes, salt and pepper, onion and cheese.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used, making sure potatoes are last layer.
Heat soup and water; mix well.
Pour over potato mixture.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Take out and sprinkle cheese on top.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Saute hamburger and garlic together.
Add remaining ingredients with water.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: apple spice muffins
directions: In saucepan, combine raisins and water.
Simmer for about 10 minutes or until raisins are plump.
With slotted spoon, remove raisins from liquid.
Save 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
To this, add the baking soda and mix together. Set aside to cool.
In a bowl, combine sugar and oil.
Add applesauce and raisin liquid.
Add dry ingredients and raisins.
Mix well. Batter will be thinner than most muffin batter.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs slightly; add oil and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add apples.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl and refrigerate.

title: cranberry pitcher punch
directions: With fork, crush cranberry sauce in can; turn into large bowl. Add water; beat until smooth.
Stir in juices, extract, ginger ale and a few ice cubes.
Pour into 6 tall glasses.
If desired, garnish with mint and clove-studded lemon circles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana cream cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, 1 stick butter and 2 tablespoons sugar. Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press firmly.

title: hot corn
directions: Soften cream cheese; add corn.
Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add corn, peppers and cheese.
Mix and add sugar.
Bake at low temperature about 1 hour.
Also you can add 1 tablespoon chopped onion.
Double or triple for larger dish.

title: sausage balls
directions: Set to room temperature.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Heat butter in a large saucepan; add onion.
Cover and cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Add carrots, celery, basil, parsley and seasonings.
Mix and cook 6 minutes over medium heat.
Add stock and flour.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low and cook 20 minutes. Process in food processor or blender.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix soup, onion, chillies evaporated milk and salsa.
Cut tortillas in squares.
Put one layer of tortillas, one layer chicken then part of the sauce.
Repeat layers until all is used and you have ended with sauce on top.
Spread cheese on top and bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.
This recipe can be made a day or two ahead and then baked if kept refrigerated.

title: crabmeat perfection
directions: Mix all but cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, flavoring and sugar together and add egg. Add flour and milk and mix well.
Chill dough for several hours. Roll out on lightly floured board to desired thickness (1/4-inch). Cut in appropriate shapes.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired. Bake on ungreased baking sheet in moderate oven (350°) for about 10 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place into an 8-inch square baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cream puffs with chicken salad
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and salt in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until butter is melted and sugar is dissolved; stir constantly.
Add the flour all at once.
Stir vigorously with wooden spoon until mixture is smooth and leaves sides of pan, forming a ball.
Turn off heat; add 1 egg and beat until well mixed.
Continue adding eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Beat until smooth; cover lightly.
Let stand until cool.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 8 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on rack.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix together the sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add the milk, margarine and vanilla.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Pour into a baked pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: zucchini tomato bake
directions: Peel zucchini and slice thin.
Slice tomatoes.
Alternate layers of zucchini, tomatoes and Provolone cheese in casserole using as many layers as you wish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs (if desired).
Bake covered 1 hour at 350°, then uncovered 15 minutes.

title: grandma varner's raisin cake
directions: Mix sugar, water, salt, cinnamon, cloves, oleo and raisins together and boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool to just warm (not hot). Add baking soda, baking powder and flour.
(If not thick enough, add a little more flour.
If you have to add more flour, use the 6 teaspoons of baking powder, not just 5.)
Grease a large long pan with oleo and flour sides and bottom.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 1 hour.

title: gruyere salad roulade(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Heat the oven to gas mark 6/400°/200° C.
Line a large Swiss roll tin (approximately 13 x 9-inches, 33 x 23 cm) with a piece of greased greaseproof paper and sprinkle with a little grated Parmesan.
Mix the breadcrumbs
and grated Gruyere together in a mixing bowl.
Mix in the yolks of the eggs and the cream. Season with salt and 2 to 3 pinches of cayenne pepper.
Stir in the warm water to soften the mixture.
Add a pinch of salt to the egg whites and whisk until they stand in soft peaks, then fold gently into the cheese mixture with a metal spoon.

title: pineapple angel cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve 1 cup juice and set aside.
Combine pudding, 1/2 cup juice and milk in bowl.
Beat on low speed until thickened.
Fold in sour cream and pineapple.
Place 1/3 of cake in bottom of dish.
Drizzle with 2 to 3 tablespoons remaining pineapple juice.
Spoon 1/3 of pudding mixture.
Repeat twice ending with pudding mixture.
Cover and chill for 3 hours.
Before serving, top with Cool Whip.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Dump cherry pie filling and pineapple into a 9 x 12 baking pan.
Top with dry yellow cake mix and pecans.
Pour melted margarine over the mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and bacon in separate skillets.
Preheat oven to 300°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, seasonings and Bisquick in blender.
Add this mix with chopped vegetables.
Fold in 1/2 cup grated cheese.
May use corn flake crumbs to thicken if needed.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Prior to baking, use 1/2 cup grated cheese and sprinkle with paprika and parsley flakes on top if desired.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix 2 cups of sugar, flour, egg yolks and cream in large boiler.
Melt 1/2 cup sugar in a heavy iron skillet.
Start both at the same time.
Stirring constantly, melt sugar to a light brown. Mix with milk and sugar mixture.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in water.
Use cold water to test.
Stir until cool enough to spread on cake.

title: low-cholesterol cornbread
directions: Sift together cornmeal, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Pour in corn oil, egg white and buttermilk.
Mix well.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix
by hand.
Bake in a long 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Slice potatoes into thin slices.
Mix soup, seasoned salt, onion powder, milk and bacon bits in a large bowl.
Pour over potatoes and mix until all potatoes are coated. Bake for 1 hour at 400°, covered. Remove cover the last 15 minutes to brown the potatoes.

title: lib hick's cherry cobbler
directions: Mix the dry ingredients and then add milk, forming a batter. Melt 4 tablespoons butter in baking dish.
Pour batter on top of the butter.
Heat berries or fruit, mixing in extra 1/2 cup of sugar if fruit is not already sweetened.
Pour hot berries over the batter.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, sour cream, vegetable oil, sugar and water. Put 1/2 cake mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle 1/2 dry mixture on top. Pour remaining cake mixture in dish. Top with remaining dry mixture. Twirl with a fork. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Glaze when cool.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: Add cooked rice to onion, shrimp, cucumbers, 3 chopped eggs and 1/2 cup French dressing.
Mix and
chill in refrigerator. Place lettuce leaves in a bowl, topping with rice mixture. Grate remaining eggs and sprinkle on top.
Mix remaining French dressing with catsup and pour on top of salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and oil; slowly add flour and flavoring.
Using spoon, drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: mexican layered salad
directions: Layer in an oblong dish as follows:

title: cheese cake(plain)
directions: Mix the ingredients and press into bottom of spring-form pan and refrigerate.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk over low heat; let cool.
Add pineapple.
Stir well.
Beat cream until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Put crushed crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add mixture.
Put crumbs on top.
Put in freezer overnight.
Thaw before serving.

title: strawberry bread with sauce
directions: Reserve strawberry juice for spread.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Make a hole in the center of mixture.
Pour strawberries, oil and eggs into the hole.
Mix by hand until all ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Stir in the chopped pecans. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Then whip lightly about 5 minutes.
Shape into small balls and cook in lightly oiled frypan until done.
Drain off juice to make gravy.
I add enough flour to thicken, then add water and a little milk.
Bring to a boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over meatballs and heat in oven until you are ready to serve.

title: jiffy rhubarb dessert
directions: Grease a 7 x 10-inch pan.
Place rhubarb in pan; sprinkle sugar over top followed by the jello (dry) and cake mix (dry); Pour the water over this and drizzle melted oleo over top.
Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.
Serve with ice cream or your favorite topping.

title: caramel bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot bottom with remaining butter.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over bottom.
Top with bread cubes.
Beat eggs with wire whisk.
Stir in remaining 1/2 cup sugar, evaporated milk, water, vanilla and salt. Pour over bread cubes.
Do not stir.
Place casserole in larger pan.
Pour hot water into pan one inch deep.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted one inch from edge comes out clean. Serve warm or cold.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican chili
directions: Use a large mixing bowl.
Empty tomato sauce into bowl, stir in chili seasoning.
Add beans.
Add onion, green pepper and beef. Mix well, but gently.
Turn into crock-pot and cook on low for 6 hours.
Or turn into Dutch oven and simmer on low heat for 3 hours.
May also be baked as a casserole at 300°
for 2 1/2 hours. Serve with crispy salad and hot bread.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Pour in large bowl.
Cool 10 minutes by rinsing in cold water.
Add mayonnaise.
Add remainder of ingredients.

title: popover pizza
directions: Saute vegetables for 7 minutes in hot oil.
Add the following to the sauteed vegetables and simmer 20 minutes: tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, dried oregano, basil, marjoram, garlic and salt.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Place in 400° oven just to melt cheese while preparing batter.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Stir oatmeal, cocoa and Crisco into boiling water.
Let set 20 minutes.
Combine flour, white and brown sugar, baking soda, salt, eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Add oatmeal mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spice cake with baked frosting
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients, add alternately with milk.
Put into 9 x 14-inch pan . Bake at 340° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 - 10 minutes or until edges begin to brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: turkey soup(low-fat)
directions: Heat some water in a pot.
Add some stones you've scrubbed a lot.
Sprinkle pepper, salt and herbs.
Let it boil undisturbed. Drop in carrots and onions too.
Let the soup heat through and through.
Stir in milk to make it sweet.
Add potatoes for a treat.
Toss in meat cubes.
Let it stew.
Let it bubble.
Let it brew.
Taste the soup and when it's done, share Stone Soup with everyone.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine; stir in
stuffing.
Use large casserole dish. Put one layer of
stuffing,
then
a
layer of chicken. Mix
can of mushroom soup
with
can
of
broth
(from cooking chicken); pour over chicken.
Place another layer of stuffing and one
of chicken.
Mix
chicken
soup and a can of chicken broth
and
pour over top.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain well.
Melt cheese in sausage.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon on English muffin halves.
Cook at 350° until brown, about 10-15 minutes.
Kids and teenagers love these. They can be frozen and used as needed.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Toss all ingredients except Ritz crackers and margarine. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix crushed Ritz crackers and melted margarine and spread over vegetable mixture. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: potato casserole
directions: Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° or until top is lightly browned.

title: a friend's fastest cake in the west
directions: Mix in pan the flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Beat eggs; add to flour mixture, then stir in oil and apple pie filling.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick fix soup
directions: Heat frozen vegetables in canned onion soup until vegetables are tender.
Serve with toasted croutons and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: helen's cheese wafers
directions: Blend ingredients together until smooth and well mixed.
Pinch off small portions of dough; roll into balls, about the size of a marble.
Put onto ungreased cookie sheets, flatten with tines of a fork and bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: mock pizza
directions: Mix together and let set for several hours.
Spread on English muffins and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat tomato soup slowly.

Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water and add to soup. Stir in cream cheese until melted into mixture. Remove from heat and add celery, bell pepper, onion and sour cream. Drain and mash shrimp. Add shrimp and mayonnaise. Chill until set, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mother's lemon pie
directions: Cook lemon pudding according to directions on the package, except use the milk and lemon juice for liquid and add water for the remaining amount of liquid.
Separate the eggs.
Beat the yolks and add to the pudding.
Keep the whites for the meringue. Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: chicken squares
directions: Mix
thoroughly;
place
even
amount in center of each roll. Pull
corners of rolls to the center.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican sunset (non-alcoholic drink)
directions: Pour orange juice into tall glasses.
Add grenadine and allow to settle to bottom.
May be served over ice.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
While mixing, add oil, vanilla, salt and baking powder and beat in flour gradually. After mixing, add crushed pineapple and chopped walnuts.
Fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 12 "GLASS" baking dish, coated with cooking spray, for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool completely before icing.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add all the ingredients together and bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Put pecans on top.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use 3 good teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: raisin-cinnamon rolls
directions: On lightly floured surface, roll 1/2 recipe Basic Roll Dough to 16 x 8-inch rectangle.
Combine sugar, butter and cinnamon. Spread over dough.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Roll lengthwise for jelly roll.
Seal edge; cut in 1-inch slices.

title: rice dish
directions: Drain liquid
from
mushrooms
and
add enough water to make 2 1/2 cups.	Combine all ingredients in large casserole. Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
